title: basil, walnut and garlic soup
directions: In a blender, blend basil, oil, walnuts, cheese and garlic. Blend until thick and smooth, then transfer to a large pot.
Add 8 cups chicken broth and heat over moderate heat until it is very hot.
Ladle soup into heated bowls and serve with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; add butter and milk in a casserole dish.
Cook on High for 4 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well until it hardens.

title: new flavor burger
directions: Mix well.
Form into 4 patties.
Grill or brown until done.

title: super gingersnaps
directions: Combine half of the flour, brown sugar, shortening, molasses, egg, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat with an electric mixer until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour. Roll into 1-inch dough balls in the sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until tops are set and crackled.

title: chicken divan
directions: Prepare
broccoli as directed on package.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Make
a
mixture
of mayonnaise, chicken soup, curry powder and lemon juice.
Then make a separate mixture of bread crumbs and margarine.
Layer in dish broccoli, chicken, cooked and
pulled off
bones,
mayonnaise
mixture
and bread crumb mixture.
Top with grated cheese and cook for 30 minutes.

title: butson soup
directions: Place beef rump and onion in kettle and cover with water. Cook.
Put flour, eggs and salt in a separate bowl and stir until crumbly, then drop into water in which meat is cooking.
Continue to cook until meat is of desired tenderness.
You may add carrots to meat, if desired.
May be served as a first course after removing the meat.
Serve meat with German potato salad, buttered noodles or whatever.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large bowl. Add sharp cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mustard, paprika, salt, deviled ham, parsley flakes and pimento. Mix thoroughly.
Chill until nearly firm.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with additional paprika.
Remove from refrigerator 15 to 20 minutes before serving. Serve with assorted crackers and bread rounds. Makes 1 large ball.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix and pour into large pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: You can put in any kind of vegetables you want but the most common vegetables are corn, green beans and carrots.
You can also put in hot peppers, if you want.
Also can add hamburger.

title: milano's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground meat with onions and bell peppers; drain any grease.
Add Ro-Tel, paste and garlic.
Let cook on low about 30 minutes, stirring.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Let cook about 1 hour.
The longer you cook, the better it tastes.

title: company chicken and dressing
directions: Melt butter and pour over dry stuffing mix.
Save 1/2 to 3/4 cup for topping.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix broth, soup, Milnot, onion and chicken.
Pour over stuffing mixture.
Add topping.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fruit custard pie
directions: Mix eggs with salt.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add milk and beat again.
Put whatever fruit you desire in it or leave it plain.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven to 350° and bake until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy layer mexican dip
directions: Use a medium size Corning Ware dish.
Spread ingredients in order listed.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar in 10-inch iron skillet.
Add pineapple; cook, stirring, for about 15 minutes, over low heat.
Cool.
In bowl, mix cake mix, oil, eggs and pineapple juice thoroughly. Pour mixture into skillet on top of pineapple mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Loosen cake from edge of skillet with a knife; turn out on plate while hot.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Mix cornmeal, flour, Potato Buds, salt and pepper with enough water to make batter.
(The batter should be a little thinner than for fried cornbread.)
Dip eggplant slices in batter, making sure each side is completely covered.
Heat oil (just enough oil to keep slices from sticking) in frying pan until hot and place eggplant slices in hot oil.
Fry until brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix egg yolks and milk; stir well and heat.
Mix all together and heat until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Add meringue.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well.
Crumble
Ritz crackers on top.
Heat in 350° oven until hot.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Melt butter and pour into 8 x 11-inch pan.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, salt and milk.
Pour over butter but do not stir.
Spoon peaches over the batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake until brown and crispy at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: slow cooker swedish-style steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces, removing all visible fat. Sprinkle steaks with salt and pepper.
Place in the slow cooker with the dill, onion and bouillon cube.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove the meat and thicken the juices with the 1/4 cup flour and 1/4 cup water.
Add the sour cream.
Return the meat to the slow cooker.
Serve over mashed potatoes or egg noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple slices
directions: Sift together flour,
1 tablespoon sugar and salt.
Cut shortening in with pastry blender or two knives.
Put egg yolk into measuring cup and
add
milk
to
make
cup.
Add to shortening mixture.
Mix
just
enough
so dough shapes into a ball.
Roll out half to 15 x 11-inch rectangle.
Transfer to a baking sheet.
Cover with cornflakes, then with apple slices.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Rinse frozen broccoli under cold water to separate.
Drain.
Cook and stir ground beef in a 10-inch
skillet until light brown; drain.
Stir in broccoli, macaroni, sauce mix, water and cream cheese.
Heat, stirring constantly, until cream cheese is melted.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or oblong baking dish, 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch.
Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: barley burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and fry into patties.
Great in pita bread.

title: sour cream noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Add tomato sauce and seasoning. Cook and drain noodles. Add cottage cheese, sour cream and garlic salt to noodles. Mix gently. Put 1/2 noodle mix into greased 9 x 13 pan. Top with 1/2 meat sauce. Repeat and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crustless ham and cheese quiche
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Scatter ham, broccoli and cheeses in pan.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: banana sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Turn into a well buttered baking dish or casserole and bake about 45 minutes or until set and browned on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Cover potatoes with water and boil until they are soft. Do not drain. Fry bacon very slowly and when brown and crisp, remove from pan. Saute the onions in the bacon fat until light brown. Add bacon and onions to the potatoes; blend in the corn, stock and milks. Gently fold in chicken. Season with salt and nutmeg. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring once. Garnish with parsley. Delicious on a cold winter night or anytime.

title: chicken sauce piquante
directions: Saute seasoning in a little oleo.
Make roux with 3 tablespoons cooking oil and 2 tablespoons flour.
After roux is brown, add small amount of water.
Add slightly browned hen and 1 can of Ro-Tel tomatoes to ingredients and cook until meat is tender.

title: orange glazed pork roast
directions: You will need 1 oven bag, regular size.

title: taco dip
directions: Smear refried beans onto a cookie sheet with sides.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together until blended well and pour on top of beans.
Add the rest of the ingredients in order and top with cheese.
Serve with tostadas.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: *I use low-fat part skim.

title: swedish crescents
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Roll and cut in strips.
Shape in crescents.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Roll in sugar while hot.

title: delicious hungarian goulash soup
directions: Saute vegetables.
Add meat and all other ingredients, except potatoes. Simmer until meat is tender. Add potatoes.
Cook 45 minutes longer.
Garnish with sour cream and green onions.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add slightly beaten eggs, add soda to buttermilk and spices to flour. Add flour and milk to batter, alternately. Add jam then fold in pecans. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until cake springs back to touch.

title: traditional fruit punch
directions: Combine juices together. Add sugar. Stir well until blended. Before serving, add chilled ginger ale.

title: homemade christmas ornaments
directions: Combine flour with salt.
Gradually mix in water and food coloring, then knead.
On a floured surface roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out shapes with holiday cookie cutters.
Use a meat skewer to make holes at the top of hanging.
Bake shapes on cookie sheet at 300° for 40 minutes.
Let cool.
Then decorate with glitter.

title: haussner's imperial crab
directions: Pick over crab meat to remove any shells.
Cut bread into cubes.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add bread and parsley.
Fold in crab meat carefully to prevent breaking.
Spoon into individual baking dishes.
Top with white sauce, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to sausage.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Can be refrigerated overnight or baked same day.
Bake, uncovered,
for 1 hour until set. Bake at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: tropical fruit fluff
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine sour cream, flaked coconut, walnuts and apricot preserves (cut up any large pieces of apricot).
Mix well.
Stir in enough milk to make mixture dipping consistency.
Chill.
Serve with chilled fruit dippers:
grapes, melon or pineapple.

title: pumpkin apple mini muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients and stir just until moist.
Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into greased tins, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 18 regular muffins or 4 to 5 dozen mini muffins.

title: chicken fricassee with herb dumplings
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour, salt, paprika and pepper; coat chicken pieces.
Cook chicken in shortening and 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet until light brown.
Remove chicken and drain fat. Mix soup and 1 1/2 cups milk in skillet; add chicken pieces. Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook over low heat until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
Stir in vegetables.
Cut 3 tablespoons butter thoroughly into 1 3/4 cups flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup milk, the parsley flakes and poultry seasoning.
Drop dough by 8 or 9 spoonfuls into hot soup mixture.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover; cook about 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy french chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper and brown in melted butter; remove from pan.
Stir flour into butter; add broth.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place chicken in sauce, cover pan and simmer until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with noodles, mashed potatoes or rice.

title: sylvia's salmon stew(quick, low calorie, and warm for a cold night.)
directions: Place the tomatoes, juice from salmon, diced onion and cubed potato into a pan over medium heat.
(Cook on low if you aren't starving and don't want to have to stir occasionally to keep potato from sticking.)

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together.
Add your rhubarb and strawberries.
Let mixture stand while you prepare your crusts. Stir mixture and pour into your unbaked crust.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine.
Cover pie with pastry; seal, flute and cut air vents.
Bake in 400° oven 40 to 45 minutes.

title: deviled egg salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill.
Spread on crackers or bread.

title: cabbage roll
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Cook rice.
Cool and mix with hamburger mixture.
Put 1 whole head of cabbage in boiling water.
Take 1 leaf off at a time.
Put meat in.
Roll; put toothpick in middle to hold together.
Fry; brown on both sides. Put in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour, steaming with water or gravy.

title: green bean - hamburger casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Place half of mixture in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Put half of hamburger meat and cheese on top of green bean mixture.
Layer other half of green bean mixture and then the next layer of the hamburger mixture.
Put "tots" on top with sprinkled grated cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: altruistic pie
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Sprinkle cherries with sugar, stirring occasionally. Sift together pastry flour, cinnamon, 8 tablespoons sugar and salt. Cut butter into flour mixture and add beaten egg.
Mix and squish with both hands until mixture holds together. Mush into ball. Wrap tightly and chill in freezer for 30 minutes.
(Do not allow to freeze.)
Preheat oven to 350°.

In 10-inch ovenproof glass pie plate, pat dough out, smoothing it up to a neat ridge at the level of the pan's edge. Put in refrigerator while doing the next step. Drain sugary juice from cherries into measuring cup. Add enough of sour cherry juice to make 1 cup. Taste. Add a little more sugar if it seems too sour.
Take out 1/4 cup of juice and put the rest to heat over a low fire.
To the smaller amount, add cornstarch and stir until smooth. Add to boiling juice and stir until smooth and clear (2 to 4 minutes). Add almond extract and several drops red food coloring.
Gently stir into the cherries mixture the
pecan halves.
Pile into the crust and pour hot juice-cornstarch mixture.
Bake for about 1 hour. Makes a general 10-inch pie. Will serve at least 8.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet, then place in baking dish.
Place 1 thick slice of onion on each pork chop.
Next, place 1 slice of lemon on each chop, then 1 tablespoon of brown sugar.
Top with 1 teaspoon of catsup on each.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes for thin chops or 45 to 60 minutes for thick chops.

title: potato-bacon soup
directions: Place bacon in a 2-quart casserole. Cover and microwave on High for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until lightly browned, then drain.
Add potatoes, celery, onions, water and pepper.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring mixture after 5 minutes. Combine 1/2 cup milk and flour, stirring well.
Stir into potato mixture.
Add remaining 2 cups milk and onion salt to potatoes.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 to 10 minutes or just until thickened, stirring twice. Yields 2 quarts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat until thoroughly mixed. Combine dry ingredients.
Add together and mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: celery dressing
directions: Saute celery, water, onion and oil.
Mix everything together and bake for 1 hour or until celery is soft.

title: quick chili mac
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Bring chili to a boil.
After mixing cheese and macaroni together, pour in the chili and mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Dip pieces of cut up apples into mixture.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all other ingredients with sausage and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a 2-quart dish. Cover with foil to bake.

title: fred's favorite gingerbread
directions: Mix applesauce and sugar together; add egg.
Add molasses and dry ingredients.
Add hot water.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: frosting for red velvet cake
directions: Mix flour and milk together.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick, adding salt.
Put in refrigerator to get cold.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and pour in bottom of baking pan.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Pour over and top with cheese. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: spiced orange toddy
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Strain.
Serve hot.
Float orange slices atop, if desired.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherries in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread crushed pineapple evenly over cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over fruit.
Slice oleo over; sprinkle chopped pecans over mixture. Bake at 325° until mixture cooks together, then cool.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: old time popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, combine molasses, sugar, water, vinegar and butter. Cook, without stirring, over medium heat until the mixture reaches 235° on a candy thermometer (soft ball stage).
Add baking soda and stir well.
Remove from heat and immediately pour over popcorn, stirring gently with a wooden spoon until well coated.
When cool enough to handle, quickly shape into 3-inch balls, dipping hands in cold water to prevent syrup from sticking.

title: vegetarian meat balls
directions: Mix all.
Form in balls or patties.
Brown in skillet with oil or bake in oven.
Serve with spaghetti sauce.

title: cheesy spoon bread
directions: Stir 1 cup milk into cornmeal in saucepan; cook, stirring, over medium heat until consistency of thickened mush.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining milk, 1 tablespoon butter, cheese, baking powder, salt and chopped pepper or pepper flakes.
Stir until cheese melts and blends well with mixture.
Stir in beaten egg. Spoon into well-greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 325° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining butter.
Great when served hot as a main dish.

title: supremes cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken flat.
Place ham and cheese on each.
Roll and coat with Shake 'n Bake.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours, covered. Remove from refrigerator 15 to 30 minutes before baking in 375° oven.
Place in shallow dish, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, bake 30 minutes.
Prepare sauce of egg yolk, soup, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix well and spoon over chicken. Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, mushrooms and fennel seed together. Mix in cooked macaroni and Ragu sauce.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brat diet
directions: For use on those times with upset stomach.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute
onions in butter.
Add cream of chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat
thoroughly until cheese melts.
Add 2 cups cooked rice and frozen broccoli.
Mix thoroughly and place in a
large casserole dish (butter sides).
Heat in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes (cover dish).

title: bacon wraps
directions: Cut bacon strips in halves and wrap around 1/2 water chestnut or 2 to 3 slices water chestnuts.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place in a single layer on a large cookie sheet or baking tray and sprinkle 1 teaspoon brown sugar on each piece.
Bake at 400° until bacon is crisp or broil 5 to 10 minutes until browned.
Drain on paper towel and serve warm.
(Can be reheated in microwave.)

title: hamburger soup
directions: Simmer on low for 20 minutes or until the rice or pasta is tender.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Assemble all ingredients and put meat in a large mixing bowl.
(Ground meat is easier to work at room temperature.)
Mix all the ingredients together throughly with your hands.
Form a roll and place in a shallow baking pan.
Lay bacon strips on top of roll.
Bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and allow to cool slightly before slicing.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can be served with cranberry sauce.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add green pepper and onion, then add garlic, oregano and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine half and half, egg and seasoning; mix well.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add cheese mixture and bacon to egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mary's noodle casserole
directions: Fry onion, green pepper, garlic and ground beef until brown. Add tomato sauce and raw dry noodles.
Barely cover with water and cook until tender.
Add ripe sliced olives, can of creamed corn and the can of chili beans.
Put in baking dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Whip all ingredients, except shrimp, together with mixer, fork or whisk until well blended.
Stir in shrimp.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours (24 hours is recommended) to improve flavor before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick cherry pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Stir in water and lemon juice and blend well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and food coloring.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Let stand at least 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: coconut pie
directions: Boil milk, beaten egg yolks, flour and 1 cup sugar until thick.
Add coconut and vanilla flavor.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat whites of eggs until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar and beat.
Spread over pie, then sprinkle with coconut.
Brown in oven.

title: raspberry custard pie
directions: Use fork to press down bottom of pie crust so it will not bubble up in center.

title: garden veggie bread
directions: Sift together first six ingredients. Cream together sugars, margarine and oil.
Stir eggs and vanilla into creamed mixture. Add vegetables and dry ingredients alternately, stirring until smooth.
Grease and flour three 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Fill 2/3 full and bake for 1 hour or until done at 350°. Let stand 1 hour before removing from pans.
Add 1/2 cup chopped hazelnuts to mixture, if desired.

title: round steak bordelon
directions: Trim and remove bone from steak.
Powder lightly with sifted flour; rub in with fingers.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat on both sides.
Brown steak, both sides, in melted butter; remove and set aside.

title: hot peanut butter openface sandwiches
directions: Place bread on paper towel, spread 2 tablespoon peanut butter on each slice.
Place in microwave on high 30 to 45 seconds. Serve hot.

title: ritzy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Add cooked broccoli.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bird's nest cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients well.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Fill and top with Coconut-Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: german apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; chop pecans and apples.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat and add egg.
Add oil.
Mix well.
Set oven at 350° and bake 1 hour.

title: sour milk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Work in shortening with fork.
Add buttermilk quickly to make soft dough.
Roll out and cut into 1/2 inch biscuits.
Bake on cookie sheet at 450° until brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherry pie filling, crushed
pineapple, sweetened condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Top with nuts if desired.

title: danish puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of water over mixture.
Form dough into a ball and divide in half.
On an ungreased baking sheet, pat dough into two 12 x 3-inch strips.
Strips should be 3 inches apart.
Set it aside.

title: english nut toffee
directions: Bring ingredients to hard-crack stage (285° to 290°), then spread on a cookie sheet. When cool, spread with melted chocolate and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Press nuts down slightly. When cold, turn candy over and do the same. Candy may break, but it doesn't matter. When cold,	break into pieces.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with bacon.
Add bacon; cook until tender. Drain off excess fat.
Add seasonings to meat mixture.
Stir in soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in sour cream and sherry and heat through.
Do not boil. Serve on noodles.
Serves 4.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add egg yolks and milk and beat thoroughly.
Add melted shortening and beaten egg whites; mix in well.
Bake.

title: celery-tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add celery and onion and 3 tablespoons chicken broth.
Cook, stirring frequently, 6 or 7 minutes until onion is soft.
If liquid begins to evaporate, add a bit more broth.
Add remaining chicken broth, parsley, thyme and black pepper.
Bring to boil, then cover, lower heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, sugar and salt and stir to combine well.
Simmer, covered, an additional 5 minutes.

title: bourbon slush
directions: To boiling water add tea bags; let brew 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add thawed orange juice and sugar.
Stir until dissolved. Add 3 1/2 cups cool water and bourbon.
Mix together and freeze 6 to 8 hours.
Remove from freezer and fill glasses with slush.
Add a little 7-Up, if desired.
Serve with spoon.
Makes 8 to 12 drinks.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and melted margarine together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: tim's pasta salad
directions: Prepare rotini as on package; drain.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, toss.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: kentucky pea casserole
directions: Cook peas for 3 minutes and drain.
Saute diced onion in butter; add mushroom soup, chestnuts and pimientos; mix.
Add precooked peas.
Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole and top with onions.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit crush
directions: Mix water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in juices and bananas.
Pour into trays or a large, rectangular pan and freeze.
Cut into chunks and put into tall glasses.
Pour chilled ginger ale over and serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add oil and mix well.
Add onion, cucumber, carrot, pepperoni and black olives.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Place in baking dish. Combine all ingredients (except almonds) and pour over chicken. Top with almonds.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and seafood casserole
directions: Coat with butter a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Put in package broccoli.
(Mix soup with wine and/or milk.)
Add seafood (crab or shrimp).
Add bread pieces.
Top with soup mixture, then cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan; bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.
This is a very quick and easy dinner!

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quilting party salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and let partially jell.
Add next 4 ingredients and let congeal until firm.
Combine pineapple juice, sugar and flour and cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Spread on top of congealed mixture.
Top with a layer of whipped topping.
Add sprinkles of coconut.

title: lime party salad
directions: Over low heat mix marshmallows and milk.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over lime jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese (softened).
Mix until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple.
Chill all ingredients before adding Dream Whip.
Chill well before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli; add olives, onion and eggs.
Combine with mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and toss.

title: lemon pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and flour; blend well.
Gradually add milk; heat until it begins to thicken.
Beat eggs.
Add the lemon juice.
Gradually add about 1 cup of the hot milk mixture to eggs. Combine the two mixtures; cook until thick.
Cool briefly.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: bread crumb pie crust
directions: Heat first
3 ingredients to boiling.
Turn heat to low and stir
in bread crumbs and cinnamon until well mixed.
Turn into 8-inch
pie
pan and press into uniform layer over bottom and up sides.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Chill and fill
with
any
precooked
or chiffon pie filling. Makes one 8-inch pie crust.

title: mexican snack dip
directions: Put in layers as indicated above, then refrigerate. Serve with corn chips.

title: apple pie
directions: Chop enough apples to fill pie crust.
Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Chip 2 tablespoons butter over apples.
Put crust over top and slit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor.
Serve with buffalo wings or raw sliced veggies.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Clean and slice squash.
Boil until tender.
Drain, then mash. Add all ingredients except 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine to squash.
Melt remaining butter.
Pour squash mixture into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt butter in microwave (about 30 seconds).
Soften cream cheese in microwave (about 20 seconds).
Mix both with all other ingredients (except cheese) in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top of mixture.
Bake until hot and cheese is melted on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Drain 1 cup syrup from pineapple and discard.
In large mixing bowl, stir in flour, sugar and soda to blend.
Make well in center.

title: catfish stew with vegetables
directions: Put catfish in 3 quarts of water. Cook until fish is tender. Add remaining ingredients except corn. Simmer for 1 hour. Add corn and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: virge's butterfinger cake
directions: Let cream cheese soften and blend with powdered sugar.
Whip the cream and mix with sugar and cheese mixture.
Crush candy in wrapper.
Tap lightly with a hammer to slice the cake into thirds, using 1/3 as first layer.
Break into bottom of a large bowl. Cover cake well with creamiest mixture.
Spread 2 cups crushed bars into mixture.
Use 2 1/3 of cake for the second layer. Follow previous instructions for layering.
Make sure crushed candy is on the top of the cake, also.

title: peach crumble
directions: Arrange peaches in greased shallow baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: 6 pounds fudge
directions: Melt in double boiler the margarine and cheese.
Mix together the sugar and cocoa.
Add melted cheese to sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan (like bottom of broiler pan).

title: hobo bread
directions: Add raisins, prunes, baking soda and boiling water.
Let stand in a covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Mix oil, salt, honey or sugar and flour. Add to fruit mixture.
Pour into 2 large or 4 small bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour for large pans or 30 to 40 minutes for small pans.

title: cherry dumplings
directions: Boil cherries and sugar 3 minutes in a skillet.
Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Mix milk, egg and vanilla together.
Add to the flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to cherries; drop dough mixture by spoonful into cherries.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: french fried toast
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 4 strips. Make your pancake batter as directed on the box, but with a little less water for a thicker batter. Heat the oil in a deep-fryer or large frying pan. Dip each slice in the batter to coat and deep-fry until golden brown on each side. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar to decorate or just dip them in your favorite syrup.

title: surprise salad - 1961
directions: Combine the jellos and hot water; dissolve jello.
Place in refrigerator; let chill to a thin cream (20 to 35 minutes).
If overchilled, there will be lumps in finished salad.
Stir the remaining ingredients into the jello mixture.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Cut into squares. Garnish with red cherries and green citron for Christmas.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding clam liquid as needed to soften for dip.

title: grandma's italian frosted cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Cool and add sugar, beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Make a well with dry ingredients and work until dough is smooth.
Take dough size of a walnut and form into a rope the size of you finger.
Shape into circles on board.
Makes approximately 12 dozen cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
If dough is refrigerated several hours it is easier to work with.

title: pizza
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions; set aside.
Fry hamburger, sausage, bacon and onion until browned. Spread macaroni cheese mixture on pizza pan; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Add other ingredients and pour jar of pizza sauce over all, adding the pizza cheese over the meats.
Put back in oven for 20 minutes.
Any toppings you desire may be used.

title: mary ann's salad
directions: Saute walnuts and noodles in unsalted butter.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Cover with powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: meatball soup
directions: Fill large pot 3/4 full of water.
Form meatballs and put in pot of boiling water.
When meatballs rise to top, skim fat.
Put potatoes, celery, carrots and onion in pot.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add tomatoes and spices to taste.
Cook for 10 minutes and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: earlene's pound cake
directions: Sift flour 5 times.
Add to other ingredients.
Set in oven while cold.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's crunch cookies
directions: Mix together butter and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Pat down with fork.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lamb and barley soup
directions: Place bone, water to cover, thyme, salt and garlic in a stock pot.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 1 hour.
Add onion, barley, carrots, beans, squash, potatoes and cayenne pepper.
Continue to simmer until vegetables are just tender, about 30 minutes.
Add orzo and cook another 10 to 12 minutes. Makes a big pot of flavorful soup.

title: salmon and vegetable salad
directions: Skin the salmon fillet and cut the fish into 1-inch pieces. Place in a bowl and add the vinegar, stirring well.
Leave to stand for at least 2 hours.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute pepper,
onion, celery and drained mushrooms in oleo. Add rice, liquid drained
off
mushrooms
and consomme.
Bake for 1 hour in covered dish.

title: easy freezer jam
directions: Mix fruit and sugar; let stand 20 minutes.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mix cold water with Sure-Jell and bring to a boil. Boil one minute.
Add to fruit and sugar mixture while still hot. Turn into jelly glasses immediately.
Cover.
Let stand 24 to 48 hours before putting into freezer.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until hot.
Serve warm with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix jello as on package.
Then add pineapple juice and sugar to taste.
Freeze.
When ready to use, pour a bottle of ginger ale into mixture.

title: little sputnicks (drop donuts)
directions: Mix ingredients together until well blended and drop by teaspoons into hot fat.
When they are brown on one side, they will turn themselves over.
Fry until golden brown on both sides. Remove from fat and drain on absorbent paper.
Shake, while warm, in small brown bag containing either powdered sugar or granulated sugar.
You can add cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: meringue fruit nests
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, using an electric mixer. Add vanilla and cream of tartar.
Add while continuing to beat, the sifted sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
When the mixture stands stiff on the beaters, it's ready to bake.
Do not overbeat.

title: strawberries in a pink cloud with sauce aux fraises
directions: Combine strawberries and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Chill until berries form a syrup, about 1 hour.
Mix gelatin with 1/4 cup of sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Beat yolks with water; stir into gelatin mixture.
Add syrup from strawberries.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves and mixture is slightly thickened, 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in strawberries, Cointreau and lemon juice.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture forms peaks.
Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into 8-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold and serve with Sauce aux Fraises. Yields 6 to 9 servings.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Put berries in dish.
Sprinkle sugar over them.
Combine cake mix with margarine and pecans.
Crumble over berries.

title: carrot soup(serves 6)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add carrots and saute a few more minutes.
Add chicken stock and cook until vegetables are cooked soft.
Puree soup and add milks (dry milk mixed with whole milk).
Return to pot and add pepper.
Heat and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except 1/2 pecans and parsley. Form ball; roll in remaining pecans and parsley.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 24 hours prior to serving.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Place in pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients; press into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: bean salad
directions: Dice everything real small.
Mix together; cover and let stand overnight.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and peanut butter; blend until smooth.
Add milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into crust and cover.
Freeze overnight.
Slice and top with nuts and chocolate syrup.

title: pickles
directions: Pour boiling water over cukes.
Leave 8 hours.
Drain well. Slice long ways and pack in jars.
Add a grape leaf to the top of the cukes.

title: 7-up chili burgers
directions: Cook beef and onion and drain.
Mix salt, chili powder, pepper and flour in small bowl.
Add 7-Up, stirring until smooth.
Stir into meat mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix
ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple coconut squares
directions: Grease 9-inch square cake pan or 7 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish. Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and margarine or butter together.
Sift flour and salt together and add to creamed mixture along with the coconut.
Pack half of this mixture into prepared baking pan.
Spread with the pie filling.
Sprinkle with the apple pie spice and put remainder of crumb mixture on top.
Pat down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: congealed cherry salad
directions: Mix cherries and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Dissolve unflavored gelatin in half cup cold water. Mix all ingredients. Pour into a 2 quart glass baking dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: toffee ice cream dessert
directions: Combine chocolate cookie crumbs and butter, mixing well. Press into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine Jell-O and strawberries; set aside. Prepare cake mix according to package directions, except use only 3/4 to 1 cup water instead of 1 1/3 cups as listed. Scatter marshmallows on the bottom of a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan; top with cake batter, covering all marshmallows well. Spoon strawberry mixture over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Let cool; cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Sauce:
Brown hamburger in a large skillet.
Add onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cook until onions, peppers and hamburger are good and done.
Drain off grease, then add Hunt's sauce.
Heat until warm.

title: pear relish
directions: Make paste with flour, sugar and vinegar.
Cook 2 minutes; add pear mixture (pears, onions, pickles and peppers) and cook 5 minutes.
Heat about 5 minutes in jars in hot water.
Seal.

title: mrs. beulah's 1-2-3 cake batter
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
May be used to make cupcakes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, margarine, sugar, vanilla and sour cream. Add
dry
ingredients.
Chill, if you want to cut into shapes. If	not,
roll
into
1-inch
balls.
Place on cookie sheet and smash
down
with
bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake at
350° until slightly brown.
Can be frosted with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar. Fold in pecans. Cover well.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour. Turn off oven and let set until cool.

title: white chocolate fruit tart
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Press into a ungreased 11 inch tart pan or 12 inch pizza pan with sides.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in frying pan or wok on high heat.
Scramble eggs quickly and remove.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in same pan.
Add cooked eggs, salt, sugar, soy sauce, chopped scallions and broth.
Stir-fry over medium to high heat for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute in oleo the onion, celery and garlic until transparent. Add 2 cups tap water and bring to boil; add crawfish fat, green onions and parsley.
Cook on low heat for at least one hour or longer, if desired.
Season to taste.
Add crawfish tails and cook 30 to 45 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels over low heat. Add potatoes and peanuts.
Let harden on wax paper.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sift all ingredients into a large bowl.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Stir eggs into dry ingredients and stir together.
Add carrots and nuts and stir well.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Test doneness with toothpick in center of cake.
Use a cream cheese frosting on cooled cake.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crab and cocktail sauce.
Mix until well blended. Spread in bottom of flat pan; spread cocktail sauce over top. Put crab on top of cocktail sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until foamy; gradually add oil and sugar. Add zucchini.
Combine all other ingredients in separate bowl. Add gradually to beaten mixture, mixing well after each addition. Pour into greased pans or greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg and mix.
Add 1 tablespoon of water and extract.
Sift baking powder and flour together.
Add to creamed ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Chill.
Form into balls. Put on greased cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of glass into circles (not too thin).
Place almond in center and brush with egg and water mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a large pan, put the peaches and its juice.
Then mix the cinnamon with the 1 cup sugar and mix well, then add it to the peaches and cook over high heat and boil for 10 minutes.
Then in a mixing bowl, mix the Bisquick, 3/4 cup sugar and the butter with enough milk to mix it to a consistency that is medium thick.
Then pour the batter into a deep baking dish and then pour the hot peaches over the batter and place in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.
Remove from the oven and serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients but Jell-O in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Jell-O on top.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add margarine and sugar.
Add nutmeg and vanilla flavoring.
Beat well.
Add milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until done.
Remove at once.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Sift sugar into milk.
Add butter and pecans. Roll into balls and chill.
Melt 1 (8 ounce) box (may take more) semi-sweet chocolate and 1/4 bar paraffin wax in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate until covered.
Let chill.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: lentil soup with frankfurters
directions: Place onions, celery, leek, potatoes, diced bacon and butter in a heavy kettle.
Saute until soft, but not brown.
Wash and drain lentils.
Add them to potatoes with carrots, sliced franks, salt, catsup and water or chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer, covered, for 3 hours or until lentils are soft. Add more water as needed.
Recipe can be prepared in crock-pot or slow cooker according to manufacturer's directions.
Serves 8.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, lemon juice, chives and a dash of pepper.
Beat well.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and bacon.
Chill. Roll one of the patty shells to 8 x 4-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Top each square with a rounded teaspoonful of filling.
Brush edges with milk.
Fold to form triangle.
Seal. Repeat with remaining shells and filling.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Chill appetizers until ready to bake.
Place in a 450° oven.
Immediately reduce oven to 400°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 32.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak raisins in cup of hot water.
Heat milk.
When tiny bubbles appear, place bread crumbs into milk.
Break eggs into blender.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla; blend.
When the bread has softened, drain raisins and add.
Also add the egg mixture.
Place in casserole.
Place a glob of butter in center.
Set casserole pan in baking pan filled with water.
Fill to 1-inch from top of casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chafing dish fruit
directions: In skillet, melt butter and stir in lemon juice, brown sugar and spices. Add fruits and their juices.
Heat through.
Turn into a warm server.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Cook rice. Mix these together. Combine corn, taco seasoning and tomato soup. Stir in hamburger and rice. Cook on low. Melt Velveeta and Ro-Tel in microwave. Add to meat mixture. Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish and bake at 350° to bubbly.

title: old-time succotash
directions: Season the chops with salt, pepper and a little sage.
Dip first in the yolk of an egg beaten with 2 tablespoons of milk, then fine cracker crumbs or cornflakes, and fry in an iron skillet for 20 minutes.

title: garlic toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On baking sheet bake bread until crisp and lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.

In small saucepan, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add garlic and saute for one minute. Using a pastry brush, brush 1/8 of the garlic mixture onto each slice of bread; sprinkle each with 1/4 teaspoon cheese and 1/8 teaspoon parsley.
Bake until cheese is lightly browned, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add this delicious toast to your favorite soup or salad. It can be prepared 1 to 2 days in advance and stored in a resealable plastic bag.

title: lithuania kugelis
directions: Place 1/2 stick of butter in frying pan.
Cut up bacon and onion into small pieces.
Cook in butter until translucent.
Peel and cut 1 potato into small pieces; set aside.
Peel and cut remaining potatoes.
Place in large mixing bowl.
In blender, crack eggs, turn on and off one time quickly.
Add the 1 potato that was set aside and turn on and off quickly.
To blender, add salt and pepper and garlic powder to taste, then more potatoes, salt, pepper and garlic powder until all potatoes are in the blender.
Add evaporated milk, turn blender to number 2 setting; blend until potatoes are coarse.
Pour blended potatoes into big mixing bowl. Add the bacon and onions and mix well.
In buttered glass dish, pour mixture and sprinkle basil on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool, cut into squares and serve with sour cream.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, butter and sugar.
Blend on medium speed until particles are fine.
Stir in walnuts.
Remove 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder in pan (8 x 8-inch square).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: potato breakfast casserole
directions: Night before:
Empty hash browns in large bowl with 1 quart hot tap water.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain well.
Beat eggs; stir in potatoes, cheeses, onion and seasonings.
Turn into greased pie plate.
Scatter bacon top; refrigerate.

title: alaskan pickled salmon dip
directions: Cut
fish
in
small
pieces
and
place in large bowl. Cover with
equal
parts	of
wine
and vinegar.	Add dill to taste. Cover
and	place
in refrigerator for 3 days.
Pickle onions
by slicing and placing in jar with Polish pickles for three
days also.
Remove
fish
from pickling and drain; dry well.
Chop both
pickled
and	green onions and add to fish. Mix with salt and pepper, then add sour cream.
Serve as a dip with different kinds of crackers.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, and butter and microwave until hot throughout.
Mix into potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato punch
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Add to water.
Add salt and cook until potatoes are soft.
Drain.
Puree potatoes in blender (should be about 2 cups).

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm, approximately 2 to 3 hours.

title: festive chicken fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with either slivered almonds or pecans.

title: coconut shrimp with orange lime dipping sauce
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar and beer, stirring until smooth.

Set aside. Dip shrimp into flour to coat, then into beer batter allowing excess to drip off. Coat with flaked coconut and set on a parchment paper lined baking sheet. These can be made ahead to this point and refrigerated until you are ready to cook them. Deep-fry shrimp until golden brown, about 2 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and top with slices of boiled eggs and paprika.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: tomato salad(excellent)
directions: Mix all except tomatoes.
Pour over tomatoes and serve. Serves 4.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake.
Mix softened cream cheese with milk and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir in cake until thoroughly mixed. Press into layer pan.
Top with blueberry pie filling. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Or, refrigerate cake mixture overnight and top with pie filling the next day just before serving.
(Put pie filling in refrigerator to chill.)

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix together, except potatoes.
DO NOT brown meat.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and continue baking for another 2 hours.

title: turkey sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into serving size pieces; set aside.
Saute mushrooms, carrots and zucchini in butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add tomatoes, water, basil, thyme and sausage. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Mix rice into liquid, cover, remove from heat and let stand 8 minutes.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken dish
directions: Mix and pour in large baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or 10 to 15 minutes in microwave.

title: pound cake
directions: Put sugar
and	Crisco	in
a
bowl
and beat, then add baking powder
and
salt.	Add eggs, one at a time.
Add 1 cup of milk and 1 cup of flour.
Another cup of flour and the rest of the milk and then the last cup of flour.
Add flavoring and beat real good.
Pour into cake pan.	Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
When soft, cool, peel and dice.
Add celery, eggs, onions, pickle and parsley.
Fry bacon until crisp and brown.
Beat eggs; add sugar, spices and diluted vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture into the hot bacon fat and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 10 minutes. Pour over potato mixture and mix lightly.
Allow to stand several hours before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poor man's stew
directions: Cut Spam in small cubes and combine with all other ingredients in saucepan.
May have to add 1/2 cup water in order to cook for about 20 minutes.
Serve with hot bread or rice.
Good quick meal.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Melt butter in microwave dish.
Add potatoes, garlic and onion.
Toss together.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook for 5 minutes on High.
Stir in green pepper, salt and pepper.
Toss again and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Mix cheese and paprika and toss again.
Cook for 3 minutes on High.
Let set for 2 minutes and serve.

title: rainbow fruit cups
directions: Mix the yogurt, whipped topping, orange juice and orange zest in a medium bowl. Chill, cover and put in the refrigerator. Combine the oranges, undrained pineapple, bananas and apples in a medium bowl and mix gently. Chill, cover and put in the refrigerator. Spoon 1 scoop of sherbet into each of 16 dessert goblets or dessert bowls. Spoon several tablespoons of the fruit mixture over the sherbet. Top with the yogurt mixture.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and saute chopped onions.
Add flour; mix until completely blended.
Heat over low flame for 5 minutes, mixing occasionally.
Add chicken broth and cream.
Mix until smooth and thick.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Mix until all cheese is melted and soup is smooth.
Add beer and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in yellow food coloring and chives.
Simmer about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve hot with croutons.

title: old-time cinnamon jumbles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift last 3 ingredients together and stir in.
Chill dough.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon (1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon).
Bake until set but not brown.
Bake at 400° (moderately hot oven) for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over meat.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or more.

title: stir-fry salad
directions: Preparation:
Grate zest off most of lemon; reserve.
Squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon; reserve.
Cut asparagus into 1-inch pieces. Slice zucchini and yellow squash into 1/4-inch circles.
Slice tomato into 1/4-inch circles.
Finely slice scallion tops.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add sugar, slowly beating until thick and light.
Add salt, vanilla and half and half.
Add 2 cups milk, stir, and pour into freezer.
Add rest of milk.
Blend in other ingredients prior to serving.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine meat, rice, spices and 1 cup tomato juice.
Core cabbage; put in boiling water.
As the leaves fall off, pull out of water, one at a time, and drain.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt the Hershey bar in microwave.
Add a little milk (enough to stir).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Cool in refrigerator until set.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed. Break into chunks and put 1\2 in bottom af Trifle bowl. Make pudding using all of the milk.

Add Kahlua. Spread 1\2 of pudding mixture over cake. Spread 1\2 of Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle 3 crumbled Heath bars over Cool Whip. Repeat: cake chunks, pudding, cool whip and heath bars. Refrigerate. Serves a good crowd. Enjoy!.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
In large bowl, combine noodles, oleo, Parmesan and eggs.
Form mixture into 3 "crusts" in buttered 10-inch pie plates.
Spread cottage cheese over the spaghetti crusts.
In skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through.
Put meat mixture over spaghetti and cottage cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella.
Bake until melted.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of pan.
Add chili; spread over cream cheese.
Spread cheese over chili.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.

title: deviled crab
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add flour, salt, paprika and mustard. Stir until smooth; add milk and cook until it thickens and boils. Stir in lemon juice, Tabasco and crabmeat.
Fill 1-quart casserole; cover with bread cubes.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Mix vinegar and oil.
Pour over salad.
Toss and serve.
Serves 12.

title: billy's cheesecake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and place the whole pan into a larger pan so that the cooking cake is surrounded by hot water.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes.
Yields 24 pieces of cheesecake.

title: mount diablo dip
directions: Mash avocados and place on large platter.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread on avocados.
Layer with green peppers, tomatoes, scallions and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips and enjoy!

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots, then slice.
Cook until tender.
Cool.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients well; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: strawberry chocolate chip shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 9-inch spring-form pan. Beat 1/2 cup sugar and butter in large bowl. Add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat until creamy. Gradually add flour and baking powder, beating until smooth; stir in 1/2 cup mini chips. Press mixture onto bottom of prepared pan. Stir together sour cream, remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 2 eggs and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla in medium bowl; stir in remaining 1/2 cup mini chips. Pour over mixture in pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until almost set in center and edges are lightly browned. Cool completely on wire rack; remove side of pan. Spread whipped topping over top. Cover. Refrigerate.

title: cranberry jelly or jam
directions: Boil cranberries until they are cooked.
They will pop! Strain skin and seeds.
Add sugar.
Keep boiling until mixture slides off spoon in thick sheets.
Pour into your jars.
Seal by boiling in canning jars for 10 minutes.
Or you can store in refrigerator.

title: marshmallow mud squares
directions: Preheat the oven to 300 degrees.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat 30 seconds.
In a separate bowl, sift the flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to the mixture and beat until well combined.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured 9x13 inch glass baking dish.
Place in the oven and bake for 35 minute.

title: orange punch
directions: Combine juices; spoon sherbet on top.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale. Yields 100 servings.

title: christmas nut roll
directions: Crush cookies to a fine crumb; add other ingredients, one at a time, stirring well.
Save cherries to decorate top and coconut to roll cake in after it is well mixed.
Make at least a week before serving so it will slice well.
Wrap in foil and put in refrigerator.

title: french cherry dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, melted butter and sugar together.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Set aside to cool.
Mix Dream Whip.
Mix powdered sugar with cream cheese, which has been softened to room temperature.
Blend Dream Whip with cream cheese mixture.
Spread over cracker crumb crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: pancake toppers
directions: Whip together.
Use the topper in place of syrup.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all together and boil until sugar is dissolved.

title: breakfast eggs(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Put in blender to mix everything.
Bake in greased (Pam) 9 x 9-inch uncovered dish at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread into pan.
Bake 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool; cut into pieces.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: juan's pan burrito
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix tomato paste and sauce mixes with 2 cups of hot water.
Add half of this mixture to the ground beef.
Simmer for 10 minutes and add spices to taste.

title: beef or venison jerky
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; brush on meat.
Layer and brush on each layer.
Layer meat in an airtight container; marinate for at least 8 hours.
Dry in a dehydrator or in the oven at 110° for 8 hours.

title: roasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread pecans evenly in pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Place candy coating in top of double boiler.
Cook over low heat until coating melts.
Cool 2 minutes; add pecans.
Stir to coat.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Frozen mixed vegetables, boiled and drained.
Place in casserole dish and add one stick of butter.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Top with one crushed sleeve of Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: floyd's killer veggie soup
directions: A total secret.
Put it together somehow in a very big pot. Cook it awhile, taste it often.
(If anyone is watching, look knowledgeable and add a dash of this or that.)
Near dinnertime, declare it finished.
Call the kids and grandkids.
They will all exclaim it to be the best ever!

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend softened cheese and margarine
in mixer. Blend and whip in the sugar.
Ready to spread!

title: dick waterman's spaghetti sauce or chop suey sauce
directions: Put margarine in pan; saute vegetables until tender, but firm. In separate pan, boil Vitaburger until soft, then rinse with water.
Combine Vitaburger, vegetables, spices, Ragu and tomato paste.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Put 1/2 of cooked asparagus in blender and chop.
Add to unchopped asparagus and water. Add 2 cups of White Sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: soft yeast pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Add crushed cereal to yeast mixture; add salt and enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on slightly floured surface.
Knead 5 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Roll into 20-inch lengths and shape into pretzels.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 16 to 20 minutes.
To reheat, bake at 300° for 5 minutes.

title: overnight cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a Bundt pan well.
Put in a layer of nuts.
Break rolls apart.
Add 12 on top of nuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 dry pudding mix. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put remaining 12 rolls on top; sprinkle with remaining pudding, cinnamon and nuts.
Combine sugar and butter; bring to boil and pour over rolls.
Cover pan with damp cloth.
Seal with plastic wrap.
Let rise 8 to 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert immediately onto serving plate; allow sauce to drop, covering rolls.
Serve warm.

title: applesauce chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well, then add the nut meats, raisins and applesauce.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or more.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and margarine.
Pour pie filling into 12 x 7 x 2-inch glass pan.
Drop cake batter over fruit in spoonfuls. Sprinkle liberally with cinnamon.
Cook 17 minutes on 70% power, turning 3 times during cooking.

title: rice and beef porcupines
directions: Combine beef, rice and seasoning.
Shape into meatballs. Brown meatballs, turning frequently.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with French toast.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
In a large bowl, beat the egg, milk and salt. Add spaghetti and toss to coat.
Transfer to a 13x9 inch baking dish.
In a large skillet, cook beef, sausage, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Spoon over spaghetti mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for ten minutes before cutting.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and oleo; let stand 20 minutes. Add sugar, self-rising flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and eggs.
Mix well and bake in greased and floured sheet pan about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Add onions and saute.
Add other ingredients.
Mix with 2 cans of drained butter beans, drained can of lima beans, drained can of kidney beans and drained can of navy beans.
Also, add can of pork and beans, undrained (I prefer Campbell's; you can use any brand).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
So delicious sweet/sour flavor.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add oil gradually and blend well.
Stir in potatoes.
Blend all dry ingredients and add to potato mixture.
Fold in nuts and fruit. Pour into 3 greased 1 1/2-quart loaf pans or mini loaf pans (1 cup batter per pan).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Bread will leave sides of pan and crack when done.
This yields 3 loaves or 4 mini pans plus 1 Bundt pan.
Keeps and freezes well.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob and cook in butter in a fry pan.
Simmer until done, adding thyme or basil during last few minutes of cooking.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion, evenly over bottom of pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender container.

title: thanksgiving sausage dressing
directions: Cook sausage, onions and diced celery in a skillet over medium heat until sausage is brown.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Fry out hamburger meat and drain off fat in a deep skillet. Pour in the spaghetti sauce and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes on low.
While it is simmering, put your lasagna noodles in boiling water and cook until tender.

Lay them out on wax paper to drain. After they have drained put a layer in a deep casserole dish then add a layer of the hamburger mixture, then put a layer of Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese, put about 4 or 5 heaping tablespoonfuls of the cottage cheese, another layer of noodles, another layer of hamburger mixture, another layer of all the cheeses, then top with the last layer of noodles.
If you like a lot of cheese, put another layer of the Cheddar and the Mozzarella on top.

title: brown rice medley
directions: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add oil; heat until oil ripples.
Add mushrooms and green onions; stir-fry 1 minute.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add peas and water; cover and steam for two minutes.
Stir in rice, parsley and soy sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.
(Low-fat recipe.)

title: polly's brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Add the box of pudding and margarine.
Bake according to cake box directions. Cool.
Mix sour cream, coconut and sugar.
Spread on cake.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt butter and mix with crushed crackers.
Set in oven 5 minutes at 325°.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, Dream Whip and vanilla.
After crust cools, pour in your mixture and top with the pie filling.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Chill.
Make 1-inch balls.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with the exception of the yogurt.
Mix lightly.
Top with yogurt.
This makes 6 servings.

title: green bean packs
directions: Place green beans on 14-inch double strength foil packages. Dot with butter and small pinch of each herb.
Cook on grill, turning once.

title: honey mustard chicken(fast and easy)
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan or grill.
Brush chicken with half of the sauce. Grill or broil 10 minutes. Turn and brush with remaining sauce. Continue grilling or broiling 8 to 10 minutes more or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple, egg, flour and sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cut 5 slices of white bread into small cubes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add bread cubes and stir until brown.
Put on top of pineapple mixture and bake 1/2 hour longer at the same temperature.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend together; roll into small balls.
Heat oven to 350°. Bake for 15 minutes.
(Velveeta cheese not recommended.)

title: barbecued ribs with sauerkraut
directions: Place spareribs in the bottom of a large kettle or saucepan. Pour the can of sauerkraut over the top of the spareribs.
Mix together the tomato sauce, catsup, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over the sauerkraut.
Spread the onion slices over the sauce.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake of your choice in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool several hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well.
Add other ingredients; mix until smooth.
Place into two 9 1/2 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll out half of pastry for bottom of 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate it and rest of pastry.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash berries and drain.
Place in bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to berries; toss lightly, then pour into pan, mounding in center. Dot with butter.
Roll out remaining pastry to fit top.
Cut a 2-inch cross in center for steam vent.
Place on top of pie and seal and trim.
Brush with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 45 minutes or until juices bubble through steam vent.
Cool at least one hour.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and sugar.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese.
Stir, then add ice water.
Put in refrigerator; when it starts to thicken add nuts, celery and whipped evaporated milk.
Whip evaporated milk with mixer until it's like whipped cream.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: linda's sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Mix all of the fruit together.
Sprinkle the jello and pudding mix on top; then stir together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: taco dip
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Add milk to the cream cheese until the cheese is soft (soft enough not to break the chips).
Spread mixture on bottom of a cookie sheet.
Top mixture with the bottle of taco sauce.
Follow with the chopped green pepper and tomato.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Chill and remove when ready to serve with chips.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until done.
Dice or chop potatoes. Cut up eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, then add mustard to taste.
Makes 10 to 12 servings of 1 cup.

title: date bread(date bread is good anytime, even for breakfast.)
directions: In a small bowl, mix yeast with lukewarm water.
Stir until dissolved.
In a large bowl, add this to warm water, stir, then add oleo and mix well.
Add salt, and flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
Knead dough on a floured surface for at least three minutes.
To knead you punch and poke at the dough, then it in your hand and punch and poke some more.

title: lettuce rolls
directions: Wash and pat dry lettuce leaves.
Butter lettuce leaves. Spread mayonnaise on inside of lettuce leaves.
Add a couple of slices of salami; spread on mustard.
Add tomato and pepper.
Roll up like a burrito and secure with a toothpick.

title: walnut caramel tart
directions: In a large bowl combine the Oreo* bulk cookie pieces, toasted walnuts and marshmallows.

title: burrito dip
directions: In skillet, brown hamburg; drain excess fat.
Add taco sauce, refried beans and taco seasoning (to taste).

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt and blend cream cheese and tomato soup in pot.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin; let cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spray mold with Pam.
Pour all ingredients in mold. Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Unmold on tray and serve with favorite crackers.

title: fresh peach crisp
directions: Place sliced peaches in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Combine flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl.

Blend margarine in flour mixture. Should be coarse like cornmeal. Sprinkle mixture evenly over peaches. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375° until golden brown and peaches are tender. Can serve with cream or ice cream.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Grate cold potatoes coarsely.
Stir in cheese, sour cream, onions, and melted butter.
Put in greased two-quart casserole dish, dot with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, for about 30 to 45 minutes at 375° until bubbly or light brown.

title: kakuma nitsuke(cooked fern shoots)
directions: Boil
3 (1-foot long) fern shoots
(yellow
haired)
in water until skins turn brown and stems
become
tender.
Peel off skins,
cut stems into 2-inch lengths
and	slice
thinly lengthwise.
Soak in water to rid off lye for 4 days, changing water
daily.
Drain
off water before
cooking.
Pour
small amount of cooking oil into pot until heated.
Put
the boiled, sliced
fern
shoots
into pot; cook for a	short
while.
Add water, if needed, then add sardines, shoyu, sugar and salt and cook until taste sets in.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler. Gradually add sugar and salt. Slowly add Pet milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thick. Add vanilla. Store in refrigerator.
Heat before serving.

title: oriental salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart jar with a tight-fitting lid.
Shake until well-blended.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve with salad or stir-fried vegetables.
Yields about 2 1/4 cups.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Empty gelatin into small mixing bowl.
Stir in boiling water. Stir thoroughly until gelatin is entirely dissolved.
Stir in ice water, pineapple, and salt.
Chill in refrigerator.
When gelatin starts to thicken, add carrots.
Pour into 8-inch square pan and chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: surprise pudding rhubarb sauce(6 servings)
directions: Cut cleaned rhubarb into 1/2-inch lengths.
Put into saucepan. Add water; cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add sugar; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
There is no need to let the dough rise.
Place dough on a greased pan and bake at 400 degrees until biscuits are browned.
Do not preheat the oven.
The oven should be cold when you put the bread in to bake.
The dough will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: yuletide cookie logs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Blend in flour and salt.
Mix in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Shape into 2-inch logs using level teaspoonful for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes; let cool.
Melt remaining chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Dip ends of each cookie into chocolate and roll immediately in nuts.
Place on waxed paper until set. Makes 8 dozen.
Our family's favorite Christmas cookie!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and oleo.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour into pan.
Spoon fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Begin by making pastry as follows:
Sift flour with salt and sugar.
Rub in 2/3 cup of lard and slowly add enough cold water to form a stiff paste.
Toss this mass onto a floured board and roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in circles the size of a saucer. Put in 2 tablespoons of prepared fruit of your choice, ensuring the fruit is thickened enough to not be too juicy.
Moisten edges with cold water and fold 1/2 of the circle over the other half, pressing together tightly with a fork.
Fry to delicate brown in deep hot fat.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until smooth, add eggs one at a time. Add 1 cup flour, cream well.
Add remaining flour and vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Beat until creamy butter, sugars, vanilla, water and egg. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix in creamy mixture add nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 minute.
Run knife through dough to marbleize.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes more.
Makes 24 squares.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello (any kind) with boiling water.
In separate bowl, add pineapple, cream cheese and nuts.
Set jello over pan of ice. When starts to jell, fold in Cool Whip.
Mix pineapple and Cool Whip.
Don't drain pineapple.

title: strawberry angel ring
directions: Dissolve jello with salt in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, stirring until thawed.
