Chill until partially set. Whip until fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream or Kool-Aid.
Tear cake into 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces.
Loosely arrange 1/2-inch bottom of angel food cake pan.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain salmon; chop very fine or mash with fork.
Combine salmon thoroughly with other ingredients.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with toast or rye bread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: party chicken
directions: Mix dressing according to directions.
Place 1/2 of the dressing mixture in the bottom of a lightly greased pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar
and
oil
together.
Add eggs and pumpkin. Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately
with	water.	Pour
into
two
well-greased
and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until it tests done.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best if made a few hours ahead, but not necessary.
Serve either with pretzels or a variety of fresh vegetable sticks for dipping.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all but mushroom soup and mold in a loaf pan.
Refrigerate overnight; unmold and slice.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Put in baking dish and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange and lettuce salad
directions: Whisk honey, vinegar, mustard, salt, poppy seed and orange juice in a small bowl.
Slowly whisk in the oil until dressing is thickened slightly.
The dressing may be refrigerated for several days.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake according to cake box directions. Use oblong pan. Punch holes in cake while still warm. Mix Eagle Brand milk with caramel topping. Pour over cake. Spread Cool Whip on top of this. Crush Butterfinger bars (very fine) and sprinkle over top of cake. Keep refrigerated. This cake can be made ahead of time and it can also be frozen.
Prep time: 45 minutes. Servings: 12 to 20 squares.

title: roast stuffed duck
directions: Fill duck with a stuffing prepared by mixing all the ingredients.
Roast, uncovered, at 350° for about 25 minutes per pound.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour on top of first mixture.
Bake in 350° (preheated) oven for 45 minutes. Cool thoroughly before cutting in squares.
Very rich.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Put chicken and crumbs in casserole.
Heat fat, cream, broth and seasoning; pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oriental chicken soup
directions: Heat chicken broth and add chicken, noodles and scallions. Simmer 5 minutes and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise, onion, egg, oleo, cheese, salt and pepper together and combine with squash.
Place in casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Cook in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate-malt cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pat in bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix the ingredients together in order given.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet that has sides or on a 10 x 15-inch shallow baking pan.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add jam and dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Add nuts and raisins lightly floured.
Bake in layers or stem
pan or small loaf pans at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma bonis' pasties
directions: Mix in bowl; add salt and pepper.
Cut dough mixture into 6 parts.
Roll into circles.
Place 1 1/2 cups burger mixture on half of circle; fold over to form turnover.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve with ketchup or brown gravy.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars together.
Fold in the eggs and peanut butter.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put all dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add dry mixture to moist mixture, small amounts at a time and mix well.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Flatten only slightly with the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
As soon as cookies come out of the oven, place an unwrapped chocolate kiss in the center.
Press down gently.
Uses approximately 1 1/2 bags of chocolate kisses.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together Russian dressing, onion soup mix and apricot preserves.
Place chicken in single layer in large shallow baking pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done, basting occasionally with pan drippings.
Serve hot with plain rice and sweet and sour sauce.

title: welch rarebit
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, mustard and salt.
Mix together. When smooth, add warm milk.
When smooth, add cheese.
Lastly, add well beaten egg slowly.
Serve at once on toast or crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in
9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° until done.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and shortening to make crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs for top.
To remaining crumb mixture add molasses, baking soda and hot water.	Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 X 13 pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over batter.	Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Fold in grated chocolate, chips and nuts.
Bake in tube pan 50 minutes at 325°.

title: spring vegetables
directions: Peel a strip of skin 1/2 inch wide around the center of potatoes.
Peel and trim onions and carrots.

(Vegetables can be prepared a day in advance and stored in separate containers covered with water and placed in refrigerator.) When ready to cook, line bottom of a heavy skillet with 3 or 4 lettuce leaves, making sure bottom is covered.
Add potatoes, onions, carrots and parsley. Pour on boiling water and sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Dot with 1/4 cup margarine and top with remaining leaves. Cook over medium heat, tightly covered, for 15 minutes.
Heat a serving dish in a warm oven.
Separate peas so they are not in a frozen block.
Uncover skillet and sprinkle peas on top.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer or until all vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Carefully remove parsley and lettuce leaves and discard.
Spoon vegetables into the warm serving dish. Garnish with fresh lettuce leaves (recommend Boston or red leaf for color).
Pour
3 or 4 tablespoons of melted margarine over the vegetables.
Makes 6 servings.

title: freezer cheese cake
directions: Mix cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Add sugar and whipped cream.
Mix well with mixer.
Place graham cracker crumbs in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Freeze for several hours.
Let sit in refrigerator for 1
to 2 hours until softened before serving.
(Also good frozen.)

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate nut fudge
directions: Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Combine butter and milk in saucepan.
Heat until butter is melted.
Add cocoa mixture; stir until smooth.
Add vanilla, cherries and pecans.
Spread into buttered pan.
Cool.
Garnish with pecans and cherries.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Mix may be stored in dry place indefinitely.
Yields 60 servings.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Chop and cook onion and celery in butter; saute.
Cook broccoli, cook rice.
Combine onions, celery, rice and broccoli. Add both cans of soup and jar of Cheez Whiz.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large, warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble yeast in water; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs, nutmeg and half of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add raisins and enough additional flour to make a soft dough.

title: microwave mini meat loaves
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly, but gently. Divide into 2 oval loaves.
Place on microwave rack (bacon rack), 1 inch apart.
Top with more ketchup and cover with wax paper. Microwave 9 minutes on High, rearranging halfway through.
Let stand 3 minutes to finish cooking.

title: chocolate lover's fudge pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in medium bowl; beat well.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: cole slaw salad
directions: Crisp the shredded cabbage in ice water, if necessary. Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, celery seed, sugar, salt and pepper.
Drain the cabbage thoroughly and mix with the dressing.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Garnish with a dash of paprika and a green pepper ring.

title: lemon-lime iced tea
directions: Let the boiled water and tea bags steep for 20 minutes. Mix together
the
sugar,
lemonade
and limeade.
Add enough water to make one gallon of tea.
Serve over ice.

title: danish sesame bran bread
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1 cup boiling water and cornmeal. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup all-purpose flour, 1 cup whole wheat flour, cereal, sesame seed, salt and yeast; blend well.
In small saucepan, heat milk, oil, molasses and honey until very warm (120° to 130°); mixture will curdle slightly.
Add warm liquid, cornmeal mixture and yogurt to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in 2 cups whole wheat flour and about 1/2 cup all-purpose flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.

title: baked parmesan pork chops
directions: Place butter in shallow pan and melt in oven.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Blend egg and milk in shallow bowl.
Coat pork chops in crumb mixture and then in egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Place in pan with melted butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn carefully and bake another 20 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Dip fruit in mixture like fondue.
This can be used as topping on fresh fruit or strawberry shortcake.
Suggested fruits: whole strawberries, bananas, pineapple chunks, seedless grapes, mandarin oranges, sliced apples.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients into large mixer bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute, scraping side and bottom of bowl constantly.

title: cottage cheese roast
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: succotash
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat, cook bacon until browned. Remove and crumble. Set aside.
In drippings, over medium heat, cook potatoes and onion until onion is tender, stirring often. Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally until potatoes are
tender and mixture thickens.
Serve, sprinkled with bacon.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into greased, floured tube pan.	Put in COLD oven at 325 degrees for 1 hr. and 15 mins. or until tester comes out clean.
Let cool for 5 minutes and turn upside down on cake plate and remove pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: russian tea
directions: Make tea, add sugar, juices and lemonade.
Melt red hots in 2 cups hot water; add to tea mixture.
Add enough water to make one gallon.
Add cloves and heat to boiling point.
Cool and refrigerate.
Heat to serve.
Great for holidays.

title: evelyn's fruit cake
directions: Grease large loaf pans.
Line with foil and grease again. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large mixing bowl, adding fruit and pecans.
Mix well.
Beat eggs and rum.
Pour over mixture.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 3/4 hours. Cool in loaf pan 15 minutes.
Brush top with corn syrup while warm.

title: ranch style
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Heat beans and spaghetti together.
Add meat and season to taste.

title: cottage oat muffins(low-fat and child-approved)
directions: Two of these make a quick, yummy and healthy breakfast!

title: potato cheese puffs
directions: Add cheese, milk, margarine and seasoning to hot potatoes. Then add the well beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; add alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool on wire rack and frost as desired.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, then pour into a greased 9-inch pie dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Then mix the next three ingredients and spread on top of pie.
Bake for 15 minutes more.
Let cool in oven with door open.
Top cooled pie with a can of cherry pie filling and refrigerate.

title: squash bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mustard sauce for corned beef
directions: Beat egg slightly; blend in flour, sugar, salt and minced onion.
Stir in vinegar, water and oil.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in mustard and horseradish.

title: yummy caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and
cream
in
top
of double boiler. Melt, stirring occasionally
until smooth and set aside.	Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter
x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking soda
and
salt together into large mixing bowl. Stir in brown sugar
and
oats.
Using
pastry
blender or two knives, cut in	margarine
until
mixture
looks
like	coarse crumbs.	Turn half of oat mixture into prepared pan and press. Bake 10 to 15 minutes
or until lightly browned.	Remove from oven and sprinkle evenly
with
chocolate
chips
and pecans. Spread with caramel mixture.
Pat
remaining oat mixture over top.
Return to oven and
bake
minutes
or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir together all the ingredients.
Stir frequently, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently 15 minutes to thicken.
Brush on meats, turning often, during the last 20 minutes of cooking.
Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: eggplant maurice
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Set aside. Place a layer of eggplant in a greased casserole.
Add a layer of tomatoes and some chopped green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle lightly with the mixed seasonings.
Add a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until casserole is filled, ending with cheese.
There is great shrinkage, so force the cover down over the mixture.
Cover and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove cover. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for another 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fragrant baked potatoes
directions: Layer 1/3 of potatoes in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 rosemary, garlic and pepper.
Drizzle with 1 tablespoon oil.
Repeat layer twice more.
Gently pour chicken broth over all, taking care not to wash top layer of spices away.

title: coca cola cake
directions: Heat margarine, cocoa and coke over medium heat until it begins to boil (watch it - will boil over very fast).
Stir this mixture as margarine is beginning to melt to make sure cocoa is wet) Mix together flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add eggs and buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add hot cocoa mixture to flour mixture and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top and bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake puffs up all the way to center.

title: 7-up pie crust
directions: In large bowl, cut Crisco into flour with a pastry blender until pea sized particles appear.
Add 7-Up and blend with a fork just until moist.
Divide into 6 equal parts and roll out onto floured surface.
This makes a very light, flakey crust.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Pour melted oleo over pecans.
Sift sugar and add gradually to milk, coconut and vanilla.
Mix with buttered pecans.
Form into balls; refrigerate 2 hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Keep hot while dipping candies.
Dip refrigerated balls into hot chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: microwave creamy double decker fudge
directions: In 2-cup glass measure with handle, combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened milk; cook on 100% power (High) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
In 2-cup glass measure, combine remaining condensed milk and chocolate chips.
Repeat microwave procedure.
Stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; spread evenly on peanut butter layer.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and set aside on paper towel to dry.
Remove stems from mushrooms and then chop stems into small pieces.
Saute onions, chopped mushroom stems and garlic in olive oil until onions are tender (glassy looking).
Pour cooked mixture into large bowl.
Add Ritz crackers, crabmeat, water, lemon juice, sherry if desired, salt and pepper.
Mix all together.
Stuffing should be consistency that will stay together when stuffed into mushrooms.
If not, add water and oil in equal amounts to get desired consistency.
Stuff mushrooms.
Place in baking dish. Cook in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until browned on top.
Serve with lemon.

title: cheesy bread
directions: Mix cheeses, onions and mayonnaise.
Slice French bread in half.
Spread mixture on bread.
Bake in oven at 350° until melted.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and garlic.
Add water, sauces and onion soup mix. Add spices.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cottage cheese.
Simmer until cheese is almost melted.
Add to cooked and drained lasagne noodles.
Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 5 minute salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry Jell-O; add drained oranges and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: tub of sh-t
directions: Bake devil's food cake and let cool.
Make the pudding.
Cut cake into small pieces and break up the Skor bars into small pieces.

title: garlic grits
directions: Pour grits slowly into boiling water and cook according to package directions.
To hot grits, add butter and sliced cheese roll and stir until melted.
Beat the eggs with the milk and slowly stir into the grits.
Pour into greased baking pan or dish and top with corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm. Good warmed over.

title: shoestring beet salad
directions: Drain the liquid from the beets and pineapple. Save liquid.

title: dutch peach cake
directions: Separate egg.
To the yolk, add melted butter and milk, then beat slightly.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat egg whites, adding some of the sugar when whites have been beaten. Continue to beat until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into deep pie pan and cover with peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar, 1/4 cup (more or less), as needed.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with cream.

title: pork chop chili
directions: Cut pork chops into small pieces (bone in).
Cover with water. Simmer until meat falls off bone.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice. Enjoy.

title: apple hermits (cookies)
directions: Blend together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating will blend in molasses.
Then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in apples, raisins, dates and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat Dutch oven over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes. Add butter and melt. Saute onions until brown, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle flour over onions and stir until well blended. Add beef stock, salt, pepper, sauce and garlic powder. Simmer over low heat, covered, for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Slice onions and cucumbers thinly.
Arrange in layers in earthenware crock or bowl.
Sprinkle each layer with salt.
Cover; let stand 3 hours.
Drain off accumulated juice. Combine water, vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved, 3 minutes.
Add cucumber mixture and bring to boiling point once more but do not boil.
Pack in hot sterile jars, seal.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: fruit salad
directions: Arrange fruit on crisp salad greens.
Top with 1/4 cup cottage cheese.
Yield:
1 serving.
Carbohydrate 10 g, protein 8 g, fat 2 g, calories 90.
One serving = 1 meat low-fat exchange, 1 fruit exchange.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt butter; mix crackers, 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Pat 3/4 cup in bottom and sides of large buttered pan.
Mix cornstarch and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Add to cherries.
Cook until thick and clear. Pour over crumb mixture in pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread over cherries.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture and bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add crushed wafers, alternating with milk.
Add coconut and pecans and mix well.
Pour into a 12 cup greased tube pan or a Bundt pan sprayed with plenty of nonstick spray.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
This cake freezes well.
It may be embellished with a glaze made from powdered sugar and milk and topped off with whole maraschino cherries and pecan halves.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: In top of double boiler, melt the butter and marshmallows.
Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl and mix well with butter mixture.
Mold into loaves and wrap in wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix together the first six ingredients.
Spread on English muffin halves.
Freeze 20 minutes.
Cut muffin halves in quarters. Refreeze if desired.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrot chunks for 5 minutes only, they need to be crisp. Cut up onion and green pepper into very small pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: cherry supreme pies
directions: Mix Dream Whip as directed on the box, then add the cream cheese and sugar and beat with mixer until thoroughly blended. Pour layer in bottom of crust.
Slice bananas and spread evenly over the mixture.
Top with another layer of Dream Whip mixture, then spoon cherry pie filling over the top and cover with lid. Refrigerate until firm.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together in a jar.
Keep on shelf until ready for use. Use 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: low-fat sesame chicken nuggets with oven-roasted fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and marinate chicken for 1 hour to all day.
Mix bread crumbs and sesame seed.
Remove chicken from marinade and let excess drip off.
Roll chicken in bread crumb mixture and place nuggets on baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 20 minutes or until nuggets are well-browned.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, eggs, margarine, vanilla and milk together. Blend well; pour into 2 uncooked pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Pies will be soft when taken out of oven.
They will firm up as they cool.
Pies freeze well.

title: spinach patties
directions: Cook and cool spinach.
Squeeze out all liquid from spinach. Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls, then flatten and fry until deep brown.
Turn over and brown on other side.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Place beef patty in foil.
Layer onion, potato and carrot on top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fold foil over and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; clean and boil until the color changes. Combine all other ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Place pepper halves in a casserole dish.
Place 1/2 slice of cheese in each pepper and fill with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put 1/2 slice of cheese on each pepper and allow it to melt.
To reheat, add another 1/2 slice of cheese.

title: german potato cakes
directions: Chop potatoes, onions, eggs, flour and baking powder in a food processor and chop.
Put a generous amount of olive oil in a pan and heat.
When the oil is hot drop a ladle of the potato mix into it and press flat.
Turn when the edges turn brown.
Serve hot together with applesauce.
Not to be made ahead or frozen.
Serves 4.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix the vegetables with the salad dressing.
Refrigerate 2 hours to marinate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first six ingredients together until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Sprinkle over cake batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Just before cake is ready to come out of the oven, in a small pan mix the margarine, white sugar and canned milk.
Boil for 2 minutes, remove from heat and add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts, coconut and vanilla.
Spread this mixture over cake as soon as cake comes out of the oven.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms.
Mound in mushroom caps and chill until ready to serve.
(Can be prepared several hours ahead.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix as directed on package.
Cool, break into bite size pieces.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Layer starting with brownies, chocolate pudding, Cool Whip.
Keep layering until your container is full ending with Cool Whip on top.
Let stand in
refrigerator 3 hours or more.

title: mamie eisenhower fudge
directions: Boil the first 4 items for 6 minutes.
Put chocolate bits, German sweet chocolate, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla in a large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over and beat until chocolate is melted and mixture is creamy.
Add 2 cups of nuts, if desired.
Pour in a shallow pan and cut into squares after set.
Makes 5 pounds.
Do not refrigerate.

title: tangy caramel ice spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter in large bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in jam and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, spice, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with yogurt, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter evenly into well-buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Frost with Tangy Caramel Ice Spice Frosting.

title: apple-nut muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside in large bowl. Mix sugar, oil and vanilla; add eggs and mix well until well blended.
Add 1/2 flour mixture to sugar mixture and mix well. Stir in apples, nuts and milk.
Add remaining flour mixture and mix just until blended.
Grease or line tins.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little boiling, salted water until tender; drain.
In saucepan, cook carrot and onion in 4 tablespoons of the butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of herbed stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining butter; add remaining stuffing cubes.
Place on top of casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange frosty
directions: Put all ingredients into blender, beat until smooth. Refreshing summertime treat.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together and toss with vegetables. Dressing can be made ahead of time, but mix with vegetables right before serving.

title: hash brown bake ii
directions: Spread potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over potatoes.
Mix soup, cheese and dip.
Spread over potatoes.
Melt second stick of oleo and mix with cornflakes. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet-and-sour short ribs
directions: Brown short ribs in fat with onion.
Blend remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour over browned short ribs.
Cover. Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Simmer until clear the onions, brown sugar, dry mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Pour over beans, bacon and bacon fat.
Mix well together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until liquid is reduced.

title: sun gold fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water. Refrigerate until syrupy.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Thaw
hash brown potatoes just enough to separate.
Mix all ingredients
together
and put into a buttered casserole. Dot with butter.
Bake
to	2 hours at 350°.
Time of preparation: 15 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan or 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Pour over crackers in large container.
Turn; stir occasionally to coat all crackers evenly.

title: snickers pie
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients with electric blender until smooth.
Add peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Add powdered pudding mix.
Blend completely.
Pour into glass pie dish and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spoon into a baking dish.
Cover dish and put into preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: tabouli(wheat garden salad)
directions: In medium bowl pour boiling water over bulgur wheat.
Let sit for 30 minutes.
Mix in a shaker oil, lemon juice, salt, garlic powder, oregano and cayenne pepper; shake well.
Mix bulgur wheat and vegetables and pour in oil mixture.
Mix well and chill several hours before serving.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves about 6 a generous portion.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix together with hand mixer.
Bake in 3 round layers at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add whole corn, creamed corn and corn bread mix.
Gently mix with fork.
Fold in eggs.
Mix with fork.
Drop sour cream by tablespoons in different areas on top of corn mixture.
Fold in with fork.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 34 or 45 minutes.
Let cool at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind peppers in food chopper or blender and drain off juice. Grind pears with the onions. Allow juice to remain in the mixture. Combine all ingredients and cook in a pot for 30 minutes. Seal while hot in sterilized jars.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: In a medium saucepan, blend the sugar, cocoa, flour and salt. Gradually stir in hot water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens. Cool slightly and add vanilla. Serve warm or cold over ice cream or cake. Store in refrigerator. Yield: 2 cups.

title: four layer delight
directions: Cream together and spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and beat approximately 2 minutes.
Pour in angel food cake pan (greased and floured).
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until done. Let cool 15 minutes and put on plate.
Poke holes with fork all over top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Drain corn and beans.
Mix all ingredients and bring to boil and simmer 1 hour.
Serve topped with cheese or sour cream.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1 cup of cold water.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, bring 1 cup of water to a boil and add Jell-O.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add gelatin mixture.
Stir and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into a pan and set in refrigerator until solid (about 2 hours).
Cut into squares.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: cucumber appetizers
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with Good Seasons.
Spread on rye bread; add slice of cucumber and sprinkle with dill weed.
Use milk if cheese mixture is too thick.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove seeds and wash. Cook beef and sausage and drain. Combine rice, meats, onions, salt, pepper to taste and Prego sauce.
Fill peppers.
Replace tops and cook in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Any remaining ingredients may be placed around peppers while they cook.

title: low cholesterol cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with corn oil.
Peel, core and slice apples and place in the pan.
Combine oats, sugar, margarine, salt and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.
One serving equals 0 mg cholesterol.

title: yankee baked beans
directions: Mix in casserole dish pork and beans, drained kidney beans and lima beans.
Cook hamburger; crumble.
Cook bacon; cut into bite size pieces.
Chop up onions and bell peppers.
Cook until tender. Add to beans.
Add catsup and brown sugar.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serving Size:
Serve with corn bread or serve with hot dogs or pork chops.
Great for barbecues or picnics.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut up all items and cook slowly in a large pot until done with chili mix.
Cook meat and add to soup before soup is ready. Add salt to suit your taste.
If available, fresh tomatoes, beans and peas are better.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of the coloring and cocoa, add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk alternately with salt and flour.
Mix soda with vinegar, holding it over bowl, as it foams, add vanilla and this mixture to batter.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 3 (9-inch) round pans, cool and frost with frosting.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and butter/margarine.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Use cookie press.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and bacon.
Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Garnish with cheese and bacon.
Serves 8. Can do ahead.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream the sugar and softened butter.
Add egg, vanilla and salt.
Beat smooth.
Spread mixture in baked pie crust shell. Chill.
Combine whipped topping, pineapple, pecans, milk and cherries.
Spread evenly over chilled filling.
Chill pie.

title: rice dish
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add rest of ingredients. Stir and cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread(squash may be used also)
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat until well blended. Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and water.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until done when tested.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Put lemon and peanut butter in bowl with popcorn.
Cook 1 minute.

title: pralines
directions: Recipe may be doubled.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted margarine.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed, pour milk evenly over top.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook packages of vegetables.
Mix with water chestnuts and put in a 10 x 14-inch buttered casserole. Blend remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle crushed onion rings on top if desired.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a baking dish.
(I add nuts in the mixtures too.)
Sprinkle brown sugar, 1 cup chopped nuts and 3/4 stick melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This is a great recipe for those who don't like sweet potatoes.

title: georgia bread pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cut 9 slices of bread into cubes. Combine with mixture until bread is soaked.
Pour into a 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or an hour.
Let cool before cutting into squares.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: hot wings
directions: Mix salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Put chicken in batter in flour.
Cook in cooking oil.

title: diet oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure oatmeal into mixing bowl.
Stir in cooking oil.
Add beaten eggs, Sugar Twin, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in raisins or dates.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375°
oven 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients on low speed until crumbly.
Save 2/3 cup of this mixture for later.
Add the water, oil and eggs to rest of cake mixture.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle with crumb mixture you saved. Now, sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool a little, then drizzle with glaze.
Serves 15.

title: tomato-rice soup
directions: If using fresh tomatoes, core and quarter them.
Place the tomatoes in a large non-reactive pot and add 1/2 cup of the rice, celery, onion, basil, tomato paste, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper, bay leaf and 1 quart water.
Bring the mixture to a boil over medium heat, then cover the pot.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer the soup 30 minutes, stirring occasionally and breaking up the tomatoes with the edge of the spoon.
Remove the pot from the heat, uncover it and allow the soup to cool 30 minutes; remove the bay leaf.
Transfer the soup to a food processor or blender in 2 batches if necessary and process until pureed.
Return soup to the pot and stir in remaining rice.
Reheat soup over medium heat. Divide among 6 bowls and serve.
Calories 111, T. Fat 0.8 gr., sodium 56 mg.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Place in a casserole as given.
Bake 2 hours at 250° to 300°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight in refrigerator to let flavors blend.
Serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and broth (I add extra chopped celery and onion to broth).
Next, layer chicken on bottom of casserole or pan.
Add croutons, then pour soup mixture over this.
Bake about 45 minutes or until browned at 375°.

title: strawberry angel food cake dessert
directions: Break up angel food cake into pieces into bottom of pan.
Make jello and add strawberries.
Let jello get almost set, then pour over cake.
Chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Heat sweet milk and margarine, hot, but not boiled.
Put sugar in eggs.
Add vanilla, nutmeg and cornstarch. Mix with milk.
Bake 7 minutes at 450°, then lower to 250° and bake 10 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles and discard.
Slice pickles crosswise (fairly thick slices).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber slices.
Mix in large bowl.
Stir occasionally until sugar is dissolved.
Place garlic slices in pickle jar and refrigerate.
This will keep indefinitely.

title: sweet dill chips
directions: Drain juice from pickles and slice thin.
Return to jar.
Heat sugar and vinegar until slightly warm, stirring.
Pour over pickles in jar.
Shake until sugar dissolves.
Store in refrigerator. Ready to eat the next day.
Wonderful.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
In saucepan, heat Coke, cocoa and butter.
Add to flour mixture, then add beaten egg, marshmallows and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes) in long cake pan.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving skins intact for re-stuffing.
With wire whisk, beat potatoes with cottage cheese, milk and onion.
Spoon mixture back into skins.
Sprinkle with paprika, parsley flakes and pepper. Bake 10 minutes or until golden.
Approximately 90 calories per serving.

title: tomato pie
directions: Slice tomatoes in thirds; sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and lay on paper towels to drain. Layer tomatoes and other ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serve warm.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and spread in a long baking dish, forming a crust.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: In a medium-size mixing bowl, mix pancake mix with water. After mixed until smooth, add 1 cup fresh blueberries. Pour 3 x 3 size circle into the greased frying skillet. Cook until brown, then flip. Cook until brown. Serve with syrup and whipped cream topping.

title: quick chicken-shrimp gumbo
directions: Drain and coarsely chop tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Cook green pepper and onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender but not brown. Stir in flour.
Add tomatoes, reserved liquid, chicken, 1 teaspoon salt, thyme or gumbo file and hot pepper sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Scrub the clams well and rinse them.
Place in a large skillet over moderate heat until all the shells have opened; discard any unopened clams.
Lift clams from the pan with a slotted spoon; set aside and keep warm.
Strain the liquid left in the pan and return it to the heat.
Add pepper and cook the liquid over fairly high heat until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Pour the oil into a small skillet, add the garlic and fry gently until golden.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice and onion on bottom of buttered casserole.
Add oleo, milk, soup and cheese.
Place broccoli on top.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover. Stir and cook 15 minutes longer. (Could substitute spinach for broccoli.)

title: kung bao chicken
directions: If you use dried mushrooms, then soak them in enough warm water to cover for 30 minutes, then squeeze the mushrooms to drain well.
Chop mushrooms, discarding stems.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Blend 1 tablespoon cold water into cornstarch; stir in soy sauce.
Set aside.
Preheat a wok or a large skillet over high heat; add cooking oil.
Stir-fry garlic in hot oil for 30 seconds.
Add green pepper, bamboo shoots, peanuts, red pepper, mushrooms and pea pods.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove from wok. (Add more oil, if necessary.)
Add chicken; stir-fry 2 minutes or until chicken is done.
Stir soy mixture; stir into chicken.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add green pepper, bamboo shoots, peanuts, red pepper, mushrooms and pea pods; cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve at once.
You can serve this over white or brown rice.
Serves 2.

title: crispy pecan shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly oil a rack large enough to hod shrimp in a single layer.
Set rack on a baking sheet.
In medium bowl whisk together flour, beer, egg white and 1/4 teaspoon salt until creamy and smooth.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine peas, onions and tomatoes in a bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Chill 1 hour or longer.

title: butter cake
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until real creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour; beat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: twinkie pudding
directions: Layer Twinkies.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Put on top of Twinkies.
Add pineapple and then the bananas.
Top with Cool Whip, pecans and cherries.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, in boiling water 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, drain.
Combine soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is hot.
Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, peas, carrots and pimentos.
Spoon mixture into greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and onion in boiling water.
Drain vegetables, reserving cooking water.
Add enough milk to vegetable water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Melt butter in skillet and add flour and seasonings; stir until smooth.
Add milk-vegetable water gradually, stirring until thick.
Combine vegetables, ham, parsley and sauce and turn into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 375° oven about 25 minutes, just until cheese is golden brown.

title: pie crust(makes 5 single crusts)
directions: Put first three ingredients in large bowl and mix well with a fork.
Add shortening and mix with fork until all ingredients are crumbly.

title: ethel's good cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, salt and soda.
Add cereal, coconut and nuts.
Chill dough; shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheets at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot.
Makes 7 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage squares
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet over low heat, stirring until crumbly.
Drain sausage well.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Mix Bisquick, milk and mayonnaise in bowl.
Spread half the dough over bottom of greased 8-inch baking pan and then spread the mix of sausage over the dough.
Spread the last dough and brush with beaten egg yolk.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy broccoli or cauliflower bake
directions: Cook broccoli or cauliflower until almost tender. Heat oven to 400°. Place broccoli or cauliflower in ungreased pan. Beat soup and milk until smooth. Pour over broccoli or cauliflower. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine baking mix and oleo until crumbly. Sprinkle over cheese. Bake until crumbs are light brown (about 20 minutes). Serves 6 to 8.

title: shepherd's pie in 25 minutes
directions: Crumble beef into microwavable (2-quart) dish.
Add chopped onion.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, until meat is pink. Break up meat and drain.
Microwave frozen vegetables 2 to 3 1/2 minutes on High or until defrosted.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Add peanuts and pretzels to chocolate.
Stir and spread on cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator for about 30 minutes.
Then break apart.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix in large bowl the cooking oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add cinnamon, soda, salt and flour.
Add last the carrots and pineapple.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: bombay chicken
directions: Mix rice, sherry, soups, broth, onion flakes, parsley, celery, flour, salt and pepper.
Saute until golden brown in butter. Place rice mixture in buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese. Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Delicious!

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in pot.
Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add onion.
Add tomatoes, paste and water.
Cook, covered, on low for one hour.
Add kidney beans and chili seasoning.
Cook 1/2 hour.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix slightly crushed stuffing mix with melted butter.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pam spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer half of stuffing mix; do not pat down.
Add chicken mixture.
Cover with remaining dressing.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: three bean and rice casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onion; put in large casserole with rice, water, beans, tomatoes and chiles.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Add peas and green olives and heat through.

title: baked chuck roast
directions: Place chuck roast in baking dish.
Pour over the tomato soup. Sprinkle the dry onion soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and serve.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk; pour into margarine.
Spread filling over batter.
Sprinkle 8 tablespoons sugar over fruit and add water or syrup.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: early harvest meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf and pat into loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Delicious topped with mushroom sauce.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Beat egg white until stiff; add other ingredients.
Stir until all are well coated.
Pour onto buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Break apart.
Cool or store in airtight container.

title: old fashioned molasses taffy
directions: Tip:
Make this delicious candy only on a clear day.
Our moms made this when we were growing up in the 1920's and 1930's.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat pear juice; add jello and stir.
Blend in cream cheese. Add Cool Whip.
Mash pears and fold into this jello mixture.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: In a large pot, melt margarine.
Season and fry chicken in pot.
Cover and simmer a few minutes after turning.
Cook rice separately.
When chicken is done, pour cooked rice over chicken in pot.
Add tomato paste with a little water to rinse can and soup.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cake for a crowd
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 2-inch jelly roll pan. Mix 3/4 cup undrained pineapple with coconut and set aside.
Work shortening until soft.
Add the sugar until mixture is creamy. Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with remaining pineapple and juice.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with pineapple topping and bake about 25 to 30 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Chill overnight. Mix salad just before serving.

title: carrot-walnut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Mash bananas and add to egg mixture with milk.
Mix salt, flour, baking powder and baking soda and add with vanilla and walnuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a large loaf pan.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and put on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Stir.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles.

title: cranberry spice cake(from vivian skeens clasen, stepmother)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add egg; stir in raisins and nuts. Combine dry ingredients and sift.
Add to creamed mixture; stir in cranberries.
Bake in 350° oven in greased tube pan for 30 to 40 minutes or in 8 inch layer cake pan.
Ice when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender; drain.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Beat soup and milk until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine or butter, sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour and add baking powder.
Add the dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and beat good.	Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: no-bake tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Put in medium to large saucepan. Drain tuna and peas.
Mix with noodles; add soup.
Cook on medium heat, stirring frequently.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Blend butter and brown sugar until creamy. Mix in egg. Add flour, about a cup at a time to blend it in. Add baking powder, salt and nuts. Take a hand full of the mixture and roll into a roll about the size of a quarter. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate. (Can be wrapped in aluminum foil and frozen.) To bake, cut into slices and bake at 375° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cook frozen vegetables for 10 minutes and drain well.
Add other vegetables.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and garlic to dissolve.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar, beating well.
Add self-rising flour and egg; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon mixture over sugared peaches.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix; put sliced butter on top and bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: dump soup
directions: Brown meat and drain. Mix all other ingredients together and simmer about 20 minutes. Freezes well.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add buttermilk and vanilla. Beat together by hand (not electric mixer or eggbeater) until just smooth and shiny.
Add butter and mix in.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring liquid and shortening to boil.
Add flour all at once; stir vigorously until ball forms in center of pan.
Cool slightly. Add one egg at a time, beating each one in.
Mixture should be very stiff.
Shape on oiled sheet with spoon or pastry bag.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until done.
Fill with seafood salad, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: heavenly angel food cake
directions: In a large bowl, let egg whites warm to room temperature (about 1 hour).

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Drain juice from cherries into a large saucepan and add marshmallows to melt, on low heat.
Then add milk.
Mix all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Add marshmallow liquid with all ingredients and mix well.
Put in containers and garnish with nuts and cherries.
Keep refrigerated.
Will make about 4 or 5 loaf pans.

title: layered taco bean dip
directions: In 9 x 13 dish, layer ingredients as listed, starting with the refried beans as the bottom layer. Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana pudding(rich)
directions: Beat milk and pudding mix.
Blend in topping and Eagle Brand milk.
Alternate wafers and bananas with pudding mix.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat onto bottom of 10-inch spring-form tube pan and bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Beat until stiff and set aside the egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat cream cheese, chocolate chips, egg yolks, sugar and vanilla together.
Whip evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold in whipped milk, beaten egg whites and broken pecans.
Pour into nut-lined pan and freeze overnight.
Let set at room temperature a few minutes before cutting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut
eggs in half; remove yolks and mash with remaining ingredients, except paprika, until smooth.	Spoon mixture into egg halves
or	in
a
pastry bag with a star tube and squeeze into egg halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake for 45 minutes or until brown, at 400 degrees.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix sauces with beef. Layer in a 2-quart casserole the sauce mixture, noodles and cheeses until gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mock chicken fried steak
directions: Combine egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, milk, onion, chili powder, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into 6 patties, 1/2 inch thick.
Roll in remaining cracker crumbs. Fry in the olive oil over medium-high heat about three minutes on each side.
Serve with milk gravy.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat celery soup.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add to soup. Add cream cheese, celery, and onion.
Mix well.
Add shrimp and mayonnaise.
Place in 1 quart mold and chill.
Serve with Triscuits or other crackers or bread.

title: mama's meatballs over rice
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, milk and egg; shape into meatballs.
Brown, then add green pepper, onion, tomatoes and spices.
Simmer until vegetables are done, about 20 minutes. Serve over hot rice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and salt and pepper together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch glass or metal pan.
Cook 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Cover with crushed corn flakes and sprinkle with melted butter.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: coconut-cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed of an electric beater until creamy. Add vanilla, beating well. Gradually add sugar, beating until smooth. Stir in all but 1/2 cup coconut. Yield: 4 cups.

title: garlic mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms well.
Remove stems (save stems for a casserole dish).
Trim under edges of mushroom caps so they will hold plenty of filling.
Combine cheese, butter and garlic.
Set mushroom caps (top side down) on broiler pan or shallow baking pan and spoon cheese mixture into them.
Put under the broiler (middle of oven) and broil until cheese browns lightly and is bubbling well, about 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Make a slit on top of pie crust to let steam escape.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve
lemon or lime jello, sugar and marshmallows in hot water.
Stir
to dissolve.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, pecans, juice
of 1/2 lemon and a pinch of salt.
Whip 1/2 pint of cream and fold into it.
Let stand to congeal.

title: chicken in crescent rolls
directions: Blend 2 tablespoons margarine and cream cheese.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Divide into 4 equal parts and place in crescent roll squares.
Brush with remaining margarine and sprinkle with 3/4 crushed croutons.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in the egg and milk.
Sift and stir in the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Lastly, stir in the raisins and oatmeal. Drop on baking sheet; bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: martha stewart's herb-roasted chicken with baked shallots
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rub inside of chicken with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Fill cavity with half of the fresh herbs.
Truss bird firmly with kitchen string.
Put chicken, breast side up, in a shallow heavy roasting pan.
Put pan in middle of oven and roast for 15 minutes.

title: aunt audrea's coffee cake
directions: Put above ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix until completely blended, then beat for a solid 10 minutes.
Grease and flour a tube pan (like you would use for an angel food cake; not a Bundt pan).
Make a mixture of cinnamon and sugar, using 2 tablespoons cinnamon and a 1/2 cup sugar.

Start filling prepared tube pan by putting a layer of cake mixture and then a layer of cinnamon/sugar mixture, then a layer of cake mixture and a layer of cinnamon/sugar, etc., ending with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.

title: buchta(poppy seed roll)
directions: Put yeast into warm milk along with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix to dissolve.
Add eggs to yeast mixture.
Then add shortening, margarine or butter, salt, flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Work dough until smooth.

title: chicken pepper pasta
directions: Cut chicken in strips.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside for 20 to 30 minutes.
Prepare vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain; set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit. Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate a couple of hours, overnight is
best.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Put 7 to 8 beans together, then roll bacon around it.
Put in baking dish.
Pour 1/4 bottle French dressing over the beans, then pour creamy Italian dressing over it just to cover.
Marinate overnight.

title: cheese chicken casserole
directions: Rinse chicken; cook in water to cover in saucepan until tender.
Bone and chop chicken.
Melt cream cheese in microwave or in saucepan with a little water.
Add other ingredients.
In large casserole dish, layer chicken, broccoli, sauce, etc.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325° until bubbly.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Stir all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.	Slice a few slices of bananas, strawberries, kiwi and grapes into 5 or 5
1/2 ounce plastic cups.
Add pineapple mixture and freeze. Remove 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring
6 cups water to a boil.	Add broccoli and onion. Reduce heat.
Simmer,
uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and seasonings,
stirring
until cheese melts.	Stir in milk, half and half and butter.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Be sure the
sign
is
a week before full moon or after last quarter.

title: aunt red bug's orange muffins
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients on high speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients with orange juice, water and pecans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed nut bread
directions: In large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, poppy seed and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat eggs with milk, oil and vanilla until blended.
Stir liquids into dry ingredients until smooth. Mix in nuts. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream syrup or honey with butter, add sugar and well beaten eggs. Beat all thoroughly, then add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake in slow oven, 350°, for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix ahead and let set overnight. Put cracker crumbs or potato chips on top when ready to bake. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water and sugar 20 minutes.
Add cranberries; add jello and stir well.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Chill.

title: company peas
directions: Drain peas, reserving 1/4 of liquid.
Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: tomato vinaigrette salad
directions: Dressing should be mixed by putting ingredients in tightly covered jar and shaking vigorously until blended.
Cover salad and chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Spoon dressing over the tomatoes occasionally.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, Equal and melted butter.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° until toasty, 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer Jell-O, yogurt, banana and fruit spread.
Top with crushed pineapple.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease sides and bottom of a 9 inch round or square casserole dish with 1 tsp. butter.
Set aside.
One at a time, peel potatoes, grate coarsely and place in a bowl of cold water until all potatoes have been grated.
Drain potatoes, squeezing out water.
Transfer to mixing bowl; add onions, cheese, garlic, egg, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan.
Pat corners with spoon.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: ham chowder
directions: Cook ham.
Add butter and cook celery and onions until tender. Add flour and water.
Add the potatoes and seasonings; cook until done.
Add the frozen peas and corn.
Cook only until done.
Add milk and heat to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zippy chicken strips
directions: Place strips in shallow dish.
Combine lemon juice, soy sauce and salt (3/4 teaspoon).
Pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate about 30 minutes.
Combine flour, pepper, salt and paprika.
Flour chicken and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: chocolate toffee brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cool completely, then cut into bars.

title: cheese quiche
directions: Bake crust only to very light brown.
Sprinkle with cheese and the bacon that has been cooked and crumbled.
Put remainder of ingredients in mixer and beat until blended.
Pour over cheese and bacon.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set in center.

title: dieter's delite
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill for 30 minutes.

title: white corn casserole
directions: Combine honey, egg yolks and butter until smooth.
Add milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of almonds over bottom of pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl of electric mixer and beat at high speed until smooth and creamy, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake until toothpick is clean when poked in the center.
Put on cooling rack and serve.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add hot water and lemon juice. Mix other ingredients together and add to gelatin.
Pour in mold or pan.
Refrigerate.

title: quick yeast buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and lard and mix enough flour for stiff dough.
Let rise.
Work down and rise second time.
Work down; put in pans.
Let rise and bake.
Let dough double its size each raising.
Keep in warm place.
These buns can be made in five hours.
Makes 24 bun size.
Do not all have to be baked at once.

title: special fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, stirring well after each addition.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Cool before adding to salad.

title: salsa
directions: Dump stewed tomatoes in a bowl and mash them up with your hands.
You may use fresh tomatoes, if you wish.
Now add all other ingredients and mix.
You can add more or less of each to your taste.
If you like it hot, add jalapenos.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and mushrooms when hamburger is almost browned.
Add garlic powder, wine or water, salt, pepper, lemon juice and consomme.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add noodles.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix in sour cream; pour in serving dish and garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together, then combine all other ingredients together.
Mix all together and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Make cookies the size of a walnut and mash with a glass dipped in sugar, or you can frost them when baked.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Best taken out at 8 minutes; they look like they're not done, but will be just fine.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix flour, cocoa and sugar. Add egg yolks and milk. Cook until thick. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and butter. Pour in pie shell and top with meringue if desired. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: potato herb bake
directions: Scrub potatoes and cube into salad size pieces.
Combine butter, soup mix and rosemary.
Combine onion mixture and potatoes; toss lightly.
Arrange in dish; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pentecostal porridge
directions: Brown ground beef and drain it.
Add together ground beef, tomato juice and beans (one can if you don't like beans) in a one-gallon pan.
Bring to a slow boil, lower to a simmer.
Add chili powder according to own taste.
Mix together well.

title: chicken stefano
directions: Combine oil, butter or magarine in large pan with garlic (minced); add chicken and saute but do not brown.
Cook (microwave) broccoli while chicken is sauteing until broccoli is al dente.
Keep broccoli warm.
Cook spaghetti.
When chicken is cooked, remove from stove.
In a large bowl layer chicken mixture, broccoli, spaghetti and generous amounts of grated Parmesan cheese, repeat.
Takes approximately 30 minutes from start to finish.

title: florida peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir only these 4 ingredients together.
Roll in ball, 1-inch in diameter.
Flatten with fork.
Bake on greased sheet at 375° for 10 to 11 minutes until light golden brown.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: bar-be-que-sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 15 minutes.
Can be doubled and tripled.
Keeps a long time in a glass jar in refrigerator because of vinegar base.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan, melt caramels in 1/2 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth. In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter and remaining 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Beat on low speed to blend. Press half of batter into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool slightly (about 15 minutes). Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over surface. Pour caramel mixture over chocolate chips and sprinkle nuts over caramel. Return to oven for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool and then refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese cake
directions: Press firmly into spring pan.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch pan.
Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan over low heat.
Remove and cool. Beat eggs in medium bowl until light.
Add brown sugar, beating well.
Blend in chocolate mix.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Spread batter into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, egg, peanut butter, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Place on cookie sheet, flatten and crisscross with a fork and place an unwrapped Hershey's Kiss on top in the center of each cookie.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brown rice chutney chicken salad
directions: Cook brown rice according to package directions, omitting the butter.
Put rice in large bowl and let cool.
While rice is cooling, drain the pineapple tidbits, reserving the juice.
Then stir drained pineapple bits, chicken (or turkey), celery, green onions and almonds into the rice.
Combine 1/4 cup pineapple juice, mayonnaise, chutney and curry powder, mixing well.
Stir into rice mixture.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: mrs. burch's cathedral window cookies
directions: Slowly melt together chocolate chips and butter.
Remove from heat and add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add pecans, cool.
Then add marshmallow; stir well, to coat.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on three pieces of wax paper.
Divide mixture into three parts, put a part on each paper and stretch the mixture into a long small roll.
Put some sugar on top of each roll to cover completely.
Roll waxed paper around mixture and refrigerate until firm, several hours, or overnight.
Slice to serve.

title: angel hair spaghetti salad
directions: Toss together all of the ingredients and chill overnight.

title: terry's shrimp mold
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp, together.
Drain shrimp, crumble and fold into mixture.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with party rye or pumpernickel bread slices.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat the eggs and add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Fold dry ingredients with pumpkin mixture.
Spread on greased and floured 15 x 15 x 1-inch pan (cookie sheet).
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans (optional).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel and let cool.
Unroll and spread on filling.
Roll up without towel.
Wrap and refrigerate or freeze.

title: canning summer squash
directions: Wash squash, but do not peel.
Trim ends.
Cut squash into 1/2-inch slices; halve or quarter to make pieces uniform in size. Pack raw squash tightly into clean standard canning jars to within 1-inch of top.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to pints; 1 teaspoon to quarts.
Fill jar to within 1/2-inch of top with boiling water. Adjust jar lids and bands.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chinese fried rice with shrimp and eggs
directions: In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil and saute rice until golden brown.
Combine soup mix and water and stir into rice.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. In another skillet, heat remaining oil and saute shrimp quickly about 1 minute.
Add eggs, stirring constantly, and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Stir shrimp-egg mixture into soup-rice mixture; heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve topped with green onions.

title: homemade vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and cook over medium heat until bubbly, stirring constantly. Cook and stir 2 minutes and then remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mixture into egg yolks and return to saucepan. Continue to cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Sprinkle flaked coconut over bottom of pastry shell. Add 1 cup of coconut to cooked mixture and pour into cooled pastry shell.
Spread meringue atop pie.
Top with remaining coconut (approximately 1/3 cup) and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and serve.
You may substitute whipped topping for meringue but do not bake.

title: hidden apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch round cake pan.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits in prepared pan, overlapping 15 biscuits around outer edge of pan.
Overlap remaining five biscuits in center.
Place an apple slice between biscuit.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french cabbage casserole
directions: Quarter cabbage and cook in small amount of water until tender, then pour off any water left on it.
Chop fine.
Saute celery, bell peppers (chopped) and	garlic	in
to 2 tablespoons butter or oil, slowly, until tender (about 30 minutes). Add this to finely chopped
cabbage,
pour in cream and grated cheese.
Mix well and
put
into buttered casserole. Sprinkle grated bread crumbs on top.
Bake	at
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fluffy white cake
directions: Beat egg whites, add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 10 x
12-inch pan at 375°.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and other ingredients.
Spread into a buttered pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar, water and cinnamon candies; boil until candy dissolves.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Use pineapple juice and enough cold water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to jello mixture.
Cool until partially set.
Add apples, nuts and pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cran-orange pickup
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth and frothy.
Serve immediately.
Good lunch substitute.
Contains 198 calories!

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a loaf pan.
Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Pat into the loaf pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: swiss cheese pie(or cheese puffs)
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Over low heat, add egg yolks and slowly add grated cheese until melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in cheese mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn down oven to 375° and bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes more, or until knife comes out clean.

title: hidden jam muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together all dry ingredients, then add oil, egg and water.
Mix quickly but well. Spoon half of the batter into 12 greased muffin cups, filling them about 1/3 full. Drop about 1 teaspoon of jam into center of each. Spoon rest of batter into cups.
If desired, sprinkle tops with a little cinnamon sugar. Bake near center of oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dutch oven bake
directions: Shape hamburger into patties.
Place meat in bottom of oven proof Dutch oven.
Add a layer of sliced, raw, peeled potatoes. Then add a layer of onion, sliced in rings.
Salt and pepper. Repeat with hamburger patties, potatoes and onion until Dutch oven is filled.
Cover Dutch oven with foil.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Time may vary according to size of hamburger patties and thickness of potato slices.

title: easy color cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars. Beat in vanilla, water and egg.

Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to the sugar and egg mixture. Mix well. Stir in M&M's candy. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 3 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies. For additional color, press M&M's candies into cookies before baking.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook; simmer about 30 minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift flour, spices, baking soda and salt together.
Add this to sugar mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add nuts and baby food. Mix well.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all
together except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased, large
iron
skillet.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese. Pour rest
of batter in skillet and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoon on a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: corn spoonbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add butter to corn mixture and return to casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all of the ingredients except bacon strips; mix well.
Pour mixture into a large baking dish or pan.
Cover with strips of bacon.
Bake 30 minutes and reduce heat to 325°.
Continue baking until bacon strips are brown, crispy and glazed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artichoke delights
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar artichokes into a pan.
Add chopped onion and garlic.
Brown until onion is soft.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add all ingredients in small bowl and mix.
Put ingredients in a 9 x 7-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Toss well and serve.

title: pooris(indian bread)
directions: Mix oil, flour and salt together.
Add water as needed to form a stiff dough.
Roll out in circles 3 inches in diameter and 1/8 inch thick.
Deep fry in piping hot vegetable oil, turning once. The bread will puff up.
Fry one at a time.

title: southern gal biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add vegetable oil, milk and egg. Mix. Drop on cookie sheet or roll out and cut in squares or use cookie cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp polonaise(good!)
directions: Cream together butter and garlic.
