Stir in bread crumbs, parsley and dry sherry.
Taste and add more seasoning, if you like: salt, Worcestershire, mace or nutmeg.
Spread the shrimp in a shallow baking dish.
Dot with the butter mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve 4 or 5.

title: $100 fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chips, butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Allow to cool completely before cutting.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef in skillet with onions and green peppers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat in baking dish.
Bake until bubbling hot.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; bake about 5 minutes.

title: instant pudding eggnog
directions: Mix all together but egg whites.
Beat them and fold into mixture.
Chill; sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: "wild rice extraordinaire"
directions: Melt margarine in a pot.
Add mushrooms, onions and celery. Simmer until vegetables are soft.
Add rice, water, teriyaki sauce and Spice Island.
Bring to a boil and let simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve as a side dish for chicken or turkey.

title: cajun tasso, sausage and chicken gumbo
directions: Dissolve roux in water over medium heat and let boil for 1/2 hour. Add cut up chicken, tasso, sliced sausage and vegetables. Bring to a boil. Lower fire to medium heat and cook until chicken and vegetables are tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours. Add green onions about 15 minutes before done and season to taste. Serve over cooked rice in soup bowls. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook meat. Mix all ingredients and cook until warm. Serve over nacho chips and top with Mexican cheese.

title: traditional pecan pie
directions: Stir eggs, sugar, syrup, oleo and vanilla together.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into frozen crusts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: white christmas salad
directions: Salad is snowy white with bits of color.

title: corn pudding
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into pan and dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top should be brown and middle firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: almond rice
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a casserole dish, place in 350° oven and cook for 15 minutes.
Then add rice, 1 can consomme soup and one can of water; cook uncovered for 45 minutes.
Then add 1 can consomme soup and cook covered 45 minutes.
Last 15 minutes, put nuts on top.
Pecans are a nice replacement for almonds, actually better.

title: pork hawaiian
directions: Place ham cubes in a 2 1/2-quart glass (microwave-safe) casserole.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, ginger and garlic powder in a 2-cup liquid measure.
Stir in soy sauce and catsup. Pour over ham and stir to coat all of ham.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook on High for 4 minutes. Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
To pineapple juice, add water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Add vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir in cornstarch.
Pour over cooked ham.
Cook on High for 6 to 7 minutes until sauce is thick.
Add water chestnuts and mushrooms which have been drained and also pineapple chunks.
Continue to cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed indian fry bread
directions: Mix the sifted flour, baking powder, sugar and dry milk together.
Add enough water to handle (it should be a little sticky).
Pour on floured table or board, then pat lightly until able to handle with flour.
Cut squares or triangles about 3 x 4-inches and put small amount of meat in.
Cover and crease together.
Fry in skillet filled with hot oil until browned lightly on both sides.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts until tender.
Remove from bone in pieces.
Place
in	casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Mix together sour cream and soups, pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle	Pepperidge
Farm
dressing
mix on top and cook 1 hour at 375°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off fat. Add pepper, onion and celery (saute in sausage).
Combine soup mixture, salt and almond or water chestnuts to sausage mixture.
Pour into large Pyrex dish. Bake at 375° until hot (20 to 30 minutes).
Can freeze before baking.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet over medium-high heat; drain fat. Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce. Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, or until bubbly.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuits on hot beef mixture. Sprinkle cheese on biscuits.
Bake 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: onion tomato pie
directions: Layer onions, tomatoes and cheese in pie crust. Combine liquid ingredients and spices and pour over onions and tomatoes. Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: dry bar b que sauce
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle on meat to taste.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into large bowl.
Add roast, chops or other meat and put into refrigerator.
Meat can be cooked in this sauce.
Can be easily thickened with cornstarch and served over rice or potatoes.

title: company casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Saute beef until brown; season.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Combine cheeses, sour cream, onion and pepper. Spread half of noodles in a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Cover with rest of noodles.
Drizzle melted butter over; cover with tomato-meat mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes. Serves 6 generously.

title: cheesiest scallop potatoes
directions: Boil 3 or 4 pounds potatoes, whatever your baking dish holds. Boil enough to stick a fork into and they are partly done.
Then drain. Put into baking dish.
Layer the potatoes, salt, pepper, butter and cheese up to the top of the dish.
Then, put your milk over that.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for about 45 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Sift flour in large Tupperware bowl. Mix yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside to cool. Mix sugar, salt and add hot water and Crisco. Simmer until all is dissolved.
Let cool.

title: chocolate marshmallow cake
directions: Beat eggs 10 minutes. Mix sugar and eggs.
Put chocolate and milk together on stove.
Boil until thick.
Add to sugar and eggs. Add vanilla, flour and baking powder and put into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn upside down 1 hour before removing from pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: bavarian pudding
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Mix strawberries and pineapple. Layer cake, fruit and pudding in a clear glass bowl with straight sides.
Repeat layers until bowl is almost full. Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: chicken creole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender, bone and cut up.
Reserve broth.
Put celery and onion in broth and cook until tender.
Cook spaghetti noodles and add the chicken along with the onion and celery.
Add mushrooms (drained), pimento and Velveeta.
Place in large casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes three 1-quart casseroles.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange green chilies and Jack cheese in casserole.
Beat eggs until thick and foamy.
Add milk, flour and baking powder and beat until smooth.
Pour over chilies. Top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375° until set.
Serve at once.

title: five layer bars(1 dozen bars)
directions: Place butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Heat on High 45 seconds to 1 minute or until melted.
Blend in cracker crumbs. Press evenly against bottom of dish.
Cook on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Sprinkle on chocolate morsels, coconut and nuts in layers in listed order.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes or until bubbling all over surface.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: swiss almond drops
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar and continue beating until very thick.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill until dough is stiffened, about 15 minutes.

title: serluan filled cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients and roll thin.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch circles.
Bake at 350° until they rise and fall.
Spread with any jam and place another cookie on top of jam.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order listed.
Fill 5 ungreased 1-pound coffee cans a little more than half full of batter.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Cool in the cans.
Snap plastic lids on for easy storage.
This freezes very well right in the can.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, sugar, salt, pepper and corn.
Mix.
Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Stir into corn mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cut meat off bone.
Trim off excess fat.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Brown meat in fat at 325° in a 4-quart kettle or saucepan.
Add the bone, water, salt, pepper, bay leaf and onion. Cover tightly and simmer 2 hours at 200° to 212°.
Water should bubble gently during cooking.
Add barley and let cook 30 minutes. Add vegetables and cook 30 minutes more.
(Total time about 3 hours.)
Yields 3 quarts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: can't stop eating 'em cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter together.
Then add next 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Then add flour.
When all mixed together add the Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Add onions, garlic and thyme.
Stir in V-8 juice, bouillon, hot sauce and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Add vegetables and simmer for 30 minutes more.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook rice. Add 12 cabbage leaves to 1 teaspoon salt/boiling water; let stand 5 minutes. Drain. Combine onions, garlic, meat, rice, eggs, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt. Place mound of meat mixture (1/2 cup) in hollow leaf; roll up, placing seam side down, single layer in lightly greased 13 x 9 pan. Combine, then pour sauce, tomatoes, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and sugar over cabbage rolls. Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes and uncovered for 10 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crust(an old indian recipe)
directions: Mix all together, then roll out into crust.
This amount makes a double crust.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for 2 days before serving.
Serve with your favorite vegetables (fresh).

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Sift flours.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and mix together until mixture resembles the consistency of short crust pastry.
Form into a round.
Pinch edges and prick all over with a fork.
Bake in slow oven for at least 1 hour until slightly browned.

title: champagne salad
directions: Whip the cream cheese and sugar for 5 minutes.
Carefully stir in the bananas and drained pineapple.
Cut strawberries in half; add all strawberries.
Mix carefully.
Add nuts and fold in Cool Whip.
Put into a 9 x 9-inch dish and freeze.
Put in the refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving or more.
To be eaten partially thawed.

title: italian green beans
directions: Prepare and wash beans.
Break or cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Place in a Dutch oven; add other ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until beans are tender.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Buy 5 loaves frozen bread.
Thaw.
When soft, form each loaf into ball and let raise.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and milk. In separate bowl, mix flour, salt, and baking powder; gradually add to first mixture. Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade pot pies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients all together in baking dish.

title: goof-ball cookies
directions: Cream shortening and 1 1/4 cups sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add sifted flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Chill dough.
Make into small balls.
Roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french onion soup by microwave
directions: Combine butter and onions in 3-quart casserole microwave dish. Cook at High setting for 10 minutes.
Stir in broth, Worcestershire sauce and pepper, then cover and cook at High setting for 10 minutes.
Stir and cook at High setting for 10 minutes more, then at medium setting for another 10 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes, before serving.
Garnish with croutons and cheese.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cucumbers, tomatoes, green peppers and onions. In a small bowl, mix together the lime juice, vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour mixture over cucumbers; toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for awhile before serving.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Add powdered sugar to mashed potato until it becomes liquid. Keep adding powdered sugar until it is like dough.
Roll out into a sheet.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll jelly roll style and cut. Chill.
Ready to eat.

title: cherry or blueberry cake
directions: Bake cake in three layers.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together for your icing.
Between layers put icing and pie filling.
On top layer, put icing and remainder of pie filling.

title: mom's banana creme pie
directions: Mix in saucepan, sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground beef in Dutch oven.
Add tomato paste and salt. Simmer for 10 minutes, covered.
Heat oil in skillet; fry each tortilla on both sides.
Remove quickly and fold over before it stiffens.
Place on paper towel to absorb oil; sprinkle with salt.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Mix 1/4 cup of the butter and saute onions.
Add onions to flour.
Add bacon bits and 1/2 of the cheese to the flour and onion mixture.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Layer potatoes, uncooked hamburger and onions seasoned with salt and pepper in flat baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup over top.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach for only a few minutes.
Saute onion in butter. Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Stir Parmesan cheese into casserole and sprinkle some on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Mix yeast and sugar with 1/4 cup water.
Set aside until bubbly.
Place flour and yeast mixture into a mixing bowl and blend to form a dough.

title: carrots l'orange
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
Drain.
Blend orange juice, sugar, lemon and cornstarch in pan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Fold in carrots and orange sections.
Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle parsley on top and add cayenne if you like it zippy!

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved and serve.

title: cheese and rice krispie goodie
directions: Cream together oleo and cheese.
Mix together and add flour, salt, baking powder and red pepper.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls the size of a large marble.
Mash down with a fork.
Bake on a cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes approximately 65 wafers.

title: kuchen(dutch apple pie)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with the milk. Pour into a well greased pie tin.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil, peel and slice eggplant until well cooked.
Drain, mash and mix with bread crumbs, onion, catsup, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and eggs.
Melt margarine.
Stir in flour, then add milk and cook until mixture thickens.
Add cheese cubes to sauce.
Add to eggplant mixture.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: *Boil yams or sweet potatoes until done; mash.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Cook package of Uncle Ben's Country Inn rice as per package. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (Use a 9 x 12-inch pan.)

title: swiss bread wedges
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch. Mix baking
mix,
milk
and
egg; beat vigorously 30 seconds. Stir
in cheese;
spread in pan.
Spoon margarine evenly over top; sprinkle with seed.
Bake until brown, 20 or 30 minutes. Cool 5 or 10 minutes in pan.
Cut into wedges.
Serve warm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes ahead and refrigerate until cold; peel and grate in a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix together sour cream, soup, margarine and cheese.
Mix with potatoes carefully.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.
Can also use frozen hash browns.

title: pineapple dip for apple
directions: Cook until thick the pineapple, sugar, egg and flour.
Cool and add cream cheese and Cool Whip.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with bread.
Layer cheese and sausage over bread.
Pour eggs over layers.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Bake for 30 minutes or until center is set in a preheated 350° oven.
Yields 8 servings.

title: yogurt dips and dressings
directions: Serve on waffles, pancakes or hot cereal.
Mix 2/3 cup plain yogurt and the listed ingredients in a medium-size bowl.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, half of the margarine, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon into casserole.
Cut remaining margarine into mixture of brown sugar, flour and pecans in bowl.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Delicious.
Serve with fresh vegetables or chips for dipping.

title: pan-fried pork chops
directions: Completely coat the pork chops by dredging them in a mixture of flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat a heavy skillet (which has a lid) over medium-high heat.
Brush the pan with a thin coat of oil.
When the oil just smokes, add the coated pork chops and reduce the heat to medium.
Cook for four minutes, then turn the chops.
Cover the pan and cook for 4 to 5 minutes. The pork chops should be juicy, but not pink at the bone.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add sugar and salt.
Stir constantly while adding hot milk.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Blend eggs into mixture. Add rest of ingredients. Blend well. Place into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana cream dessert
directions: Toss bananas with lemon juice; drain well and set aside. In a bowl, combine the cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into a greased 9-inch spring-form pan. In a small mixing bowl, beat the sour cream and pudding mix on low speed for 2 minutes. Fold in bananas and whipped topping. Pour into prepared crust. Chill for up to 6 hours; sprinkle with pecans.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix water, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Dip ice cream and add several scoops to float on punch mixture in punch bowl.
Then pour ginger ale over ice cream. Serves 50 people.

title: italian style pasta salad
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Add enough Italian dressing to coat well.
Pasta may absorb some dressing.
Add more Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Let stand for a couple of hours so flavors can blend.

title: heidelberg soup
directions: Cook
bacon
and
save one tablespoon of the drippings. Fry the
onions and salami in the bacon drippings.
Mix all of ingredients in
soup
pan.
Cook
over medium heat.
Serve hot with crusty bread.

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: Mix and mold into pie pan (saving some crumbs for top of pie later).
Chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread the rolls onto jelly roll pan and bake.
Mix the cream cheese, dressing, mayonnaise and sour cream. Spread this over the baked crescent rolls.
Add the carrots, broccoli, cauliflower and celery in layers. Add the green pepper and onion.
Top with the cheese and tomatoes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put dry beef on bottom of pan.
Wrap bacon around chicken.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours and 30 minutes, covered.

title: hungarian chicken paprika and dumplings
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add chicken and fry until very lightly browned.
Add water to cover.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole with wild rice
directions: Combine long grain and wild
rice
and water in a 2 1/2 quart casserole.	Add salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken on top of rice mixture.
Bake, covered,
1 1/4 hours at 375° or until chicken is done.
Combine
soup
and
milk.
When casserole is done,
pour soup
mixture
over
casserole.
Return
to
oven, uncovered, and bake until soup is bubbly.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and oleo together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan on bottom only.

title: burrito bake
directions: Grease pie plate or pan.
Mix Bisquick, water and refried beans.
Spread in plate or pan.
Layer remaining ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: arizona quiche
directions: Cut the fish into 2-inch pieces.
Place the fish, salt, onion and dill weed in a large pot and cover with the water.
Bring to the boiling point and simmer (with boiling) until the fish flakes when pierced with a fork, but does not fall apart.
Drain, reserving the liquid to use as stock for boiling the potatoes. Put the potatoes in a saucepan; add the fish stock and cook until tender.
Pour the potatoes and stock back into the pan with the cooked fish and add milk.
Simmer slowly (do not boil) for about 20 minutes.
Pour into a tureen dish and dot with butter.
Garnish with the chives or fresh dill top.
Serves about 6.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in containers.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Mix with 2 liters of 7-Up or Sprite and serve.

title: jim's chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts thin.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Take each piece and lay 1 piece of ham and 1 piece of cheese.
Roll up. Put 1 or 2 strips of bacon around it and hold with a toothpick. Bake, uncovered, for about 20 or 30 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Saute the beef, onion and peppers.
Drain and add beans, juice and dry soup mix.
Combine cabbage and beef mixture.
Cook several hours at a slow simmer.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Pout into buttered casserole. Top with the mixed chips and grated cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and Eagle Brand milk.
Add walnuts or pecans and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: sweet potato candy
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and salt in large boiler.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball
stage. Remove from heat and let cool to medium warm.
Add sweet
potatoes
and beat well until it loses gloss.
Add pecans, mix
well
and
pour
in buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Layer in pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped peas
directions: Brown bacon and diced onion.
Stir in flour.
Add milk, seasonings and peas.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole; top with buttered cracker crumbs (Club crackers are good).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white rice
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring only once or twice.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 14 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir with fork.
Cover and let steam for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces.

In 10-inch skillet with oven-safe handle (or cover skillet handle with heavy-duty foil when baking in oven later) over medium heat, in hot margarine or butter, cook chicken breasts, half at a time, until lightly browned.
With slotted spoon, remove chicken to bowl.
Preheat oven to 400°.

In drippings remaining in skillet, cook onion until tender. In cup, stir cornstarch and 3/4 cup water until smooth. Add cornstarch mixture, frozen vegetables, bouillon, half and half, mustard, rosemary, salt and pepper to skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Stir in chicken. Remove skillet from heat.

title: sesame tuna patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, except seed.
Mix well.
Form into 4 patties.
Sprinkle with seed; press in place on pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn over once.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Drain before serving.
You can add 2 cups baby lima beans. Combine and toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Whisk
together oil, dressing, soy sauce, honey, garlic and sesame
seed.
Toss
cabbage, grapes and apple slices with dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pilav
directions: In a pan, melt butter.
Add garlic.
When it turns yellow, add orzo (2 to 3 tablespoons) or spaghetti broken into rice-sized pieces.
Stir over medium heat until rice is coated with butter and smells like popcorn.
When it is turning brown (don't let it burn), add the broth which has been heated with the salt if necessary. Quickly stir once.
Put lid on firmly and reduce heat to lowest possible and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Remove from heat.
Fluff with fork and add chopped parsley.

title: golden cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Blanch for 10 minutes. Drain flowerets and place in a shallow baking dish that can go under a broiler.

title: veg-all vegetable casserole
directions: Set crackers aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cracker crumbs and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: oven steamed chicken
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Place bacon on bottom of pan, then lay chicken pieces.
Next, place vegetables around chicken; add tomatoes.
Season and place cubes around and add warm water. Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownie pie
directions: Use pie pan.
Make brownies as directed.
When cooled, mix icing as directed and ice brownies in pie pan (may also decorate for parties).
Warning:
Very rich!

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Combine all ingredients and melt over low heat.
Stir continuously and boil 10 minutes or until it runs smooth from spoon.
Scatter nuts on unbuttered plate and pour candy over them.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, mustard and egg with a little water to smooth.
Heat pineapple and lemon juice.
Add mixture; cook until nearly thick.
Add butter; cook until smooth.
Cool.
Add the marshmallows and the fruit.
Fold in whipped cream.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: chicken and broccoli skillet casserole
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook until well done.
Remove chicken.
Add garlic to butter and saute.
When chicken is cool enough, dice into bite size pieces.
Add chopped up broccoli and package of dry noodles to butter, stirring frequently until completely coated. Add chicken broth.
Over high heat, bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add chicken. Cover and cook until noodles and broccoli are tender and all liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry dream
directions: Mix first four ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When brown, press half of mixture in pan.
Save half for top of dessert.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all together for 15 minutes.
Very tasty!

title: country pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot Wesson oil in large pan.
Add water and bay leaf; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions, carrots and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Add parsley.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in sour cream. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: christmas crescents
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape big teaspoonfuls of dough into crescent shapes.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar and again when cool.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until tender. Drain well and set aside.
Melt margarine, add garlic cheese links, mushroom soup and onion.
Cook until all ingredients are thickened.
Add the drained broccoli and stir.
Serve with rye melba rounds.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: In a shallow dish or on wax paper, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Evenly coat chops with seasoned flour; set aside.
In medium skillet, cook coated chops in hot butter 5 minutes, until brown on both sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Add broth or wine; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Remove cover and add mushrooms.
Cook 5 more minutes, stirring occasionally, until chops are fully cooked. Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: how to cook a christmas turkey
directions: Cook 10 minutes at 10° in oven.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Combine basil, oregano, salt, pepper and bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in eggs then in bread crumb mixture.
In skillet, heat 3 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken.
Pour remaining sauce on chicken.
Top with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball(make 2 days ahead)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Let it chill.
Roll in a ball and then roll in another 1/2 cup of chopped pecans.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream together the cream cheese, Ricotta and sugar.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour, butter, cornstarch and vanilla and beat the mixture until well blended.
Fold in the sour cream.
Pour the batter into an ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake on middle rack of oven for one hour at 325°.
(Cake will be soft in the center.)
Turn off the heat but do not open the door! Let cake set in the oven for two hours.
Remove from oven and let cool completely in the pan.
Chill the cake, loosely wrapped, for at least 2 hours.
Remove the sides of pan and transfer cake to a cake stand or plate.

title: pan-grilled catfish fillets
directions: In large skillet over medium burner, place oleo/butter and melt, then put in onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender, stirring occasionally, then pull to one side and place catfish fillets in skillet, one at a time.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and seasoning salt, then pull onion and green pepper on top of filets and cook until done, about 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: In large bowl, mix Jell-O with Cool Whip using wooden spoon. Add other ingredients.
Pour in long glass cake pan (8 x 11-inch). Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.
Steam squash and onions until soft.
Layer stuffing, soup mixture and squash-onions until all used.
Top with stuffing.
Bake for 30 minutes in baking dish at 350°.

title: homemade stickers
directions: Combine.
Use sponge brush; coat back of stickers.
Allow to dry.
When dry, coat again.
Can make your own post-its this way.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Combine apples, eggs, oil, sugar, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Shred potatoes into cold water; drain well.
Combine with onion, salt and pepper in medium mixing bowl.
Melt Crisco or margarine in large skillet.
Add potatoes; spread evenly in pan. Cook over medium-high heat 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown and tender, turning potatoes with spatula after half the time.

title: orange penuche
directions: Cook the sugar, brown sugar and milk to firm ball (240°). Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until creamy. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mark into squares.
Makes 24 pieces.
Mighty good!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into small balls.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks together; add 1 cup sugar and mix together.
Take 1/4 cup sugar and add flour, cocoa and salt. Add to egg and flour mixture.
Add milk and mix together.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Make meringue from 3 egg whites beaten until stiff; add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar, 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put on pie and brown in 350° oven.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs, mixing well. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add prunes, nuts and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 13x9 cake pan. Cool. Prepare pudding according to the directions on package and pour over cooled cake.
The pudding will be thick.
Put Cool Whip on top of the pudding layer, and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mom's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix together cheese, margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Keep an eye on it!

title: sugarless banana-walnut bread
directions: Sift flour and soda; add oil and sugar substitute.
Mix well until light.
Beat in eggs and remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together and add egg yolks; mix, then add milk.
Cook until thickened.
(I cook mine in the microwave.)
Add margarine and vanilla.
Mix until margarine is melted.
Pour into baked pie shell and add meringue.
Brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix soups, milk, chilies and 1/2 of cheese together.
In a skillet, saute ground beef and onions together until beef is cooked thoroughly.
Crush Doritos and add together with meat to the soup mixture.
Pour into a large casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Blend margarine and 1 cup sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time. Add almond extract.
Mix together dry ingredients; add to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Blend just to mix.
Fold in peel and poppy seed.
Pour into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 70 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar; spoon over hot loaf.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours before slicing.

title: omelet casserole
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add to beaten eggs.
Mix onion, green pepper, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese, mushrooms and melted margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Put tomato slices on top, pressing gently with a fork.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 450° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
May be made the day before and refrigerated.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, oil and eggs together.
Add corn, onion, sour cream, peppers and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: low fat fluffy pancakes
directions: Combine yogurt and egg.
Mix well.
Add pancake mix and blend just to combine.
Lightly spray a non-stick pan or griddle and ladle 2 tablespoons of batter per pancake.
While pancakes are cooking on the first side sprinkle with blueberries, raspberries or banana slices.
When pancakes are firm, turn pancakes and cook one more minute.
Serve with warm syrup.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut up cabbage into small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Stir in rice. Heat soup and water and pour over meat.
Pour soup mixture over cabbage and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla and spread in dish. Immediately before serving, put 1/2 cup crushed peanuts on top. Arrange sliced apples around outside of dish. Enjoy.

title: creamy cucumbers(this is a great tasting cucumber recipe.)
directions: In a medium sized bowl, mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: apple raisin stir-fry
directions: Spray large frying pan with some butter spray.
Dice up your apple.
Add apple, raisins and rice (cooked) to the warmed frying pan.
Just simply heat up and serve.
Can add some sugar or sweetener.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage in boiling pan of water on stove.
Boil until tender.
Dice onion; put onion into a skillet with butter.
Mix onion in a large bowl with hamburger, rice, egg and a dash of salt and pepper.
When cabbage leaves are done, take a ball of hamburger mixture and wrap with a cabbage leaf.
Place a toothpick through it to hold together.
Place cabbage rolls in a large kettle.
Pour tomato juice over rolls.
Cook on top of stove for 45 minutes.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Measure bread cubes into a large bowl. Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet. Cook celery and onions until soft. Pour over bread cubes. Heat 1/2 cup butter in skillet; add oysters and liquid. Heat a few minutes; remove oysters. Pour liquid over bread cubes. Chop oysters; add to bread cubes mixture. Add milk, sage, salt and pepper. Mix well. Stuff lightly into turkey. Makes enough for a 16 to 18 pound turkey.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Place the prepared, but raw, potatoes and onions in a 9 x 12-inch greased casserole dish.
Mix the soup and milk.
Sprinkle potatoes and onions with salt and pepper.
Place pork chops on top. Pour soup mixture over all and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. (Cover with foil and bake 1 hour, then uncover and brown the last 30 minutes.)

title: cream puffs
directions: Put shortening and water in 2-quart pan. Bring to a boil.
Add flour, then cook until thick. Stir constantly. When mixture gathers into a mass, remove from heat.
Let cool for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Place in mounds on a greased cookie sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.
Yields 12 large puffs.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook two cups grits in 1 1/2 qts of water until done.
Add 1/2 cup milk, 2 rolls garlic cheese, 4 eggs (beaten), 1/4 lb butter, and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread the 2 cans of bean dip for bottom layer.
Next, mix together the mayo and sour cream with taco seasoning mix (I usually double these amounts); layer over bean dip.
Next, add chopped onion, grated sharp cheese, sliced black olives and chopped tomato.
Add any other preferred toppings.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together margarine, both sugars and peanut butter.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spread in 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread chocolate chips over top and let melt.

title: filipino lo mein(pancit)
directions: Will need 1 wok or any frying pan.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and jello together.
Add hot water, then cold water; mix well.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Put in refrigerator. Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: homemade nut rolls
directions: Mix together well, then take it out to floured board.
Divide into portions and let it stand about 1 hour.
When risen, roll out.
Makes 6 to 9 rolls.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: 5 spice casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add onion and cook until tender.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, soup and rice. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Spoon into casserole and top with cheese. Place in oven until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old time peppermint cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs, and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture. Add candy.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely and frost.

title: spicy marinara sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in the liquid Butter Buds until onion is golden brown. Add tomatoes and juice, basil, red pepper, mushrooms and the can of spaghetti sauce. Simmer about 15 minutes. You can add ground turkey, seafood or chicken to this sauce and serve over pasta. Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream sugar with butter until light.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in grated rind and juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in lightly.
Prebake pie shell in 425° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Add flour slowly; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken breast
directions: Dilute approximately 1/3 can of soup with about 1/4 cup milk and
blend.
Dip
breast into soup, coating well.
Press skinned side
into stuffing mix to which you have added onion and parsley flakes.
Place coated chicken, crumb side up, into shallow
baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour or until done at 350°. Serve
with
sauce made from heating (not boiling) equal parts of soup and sour cream.

title: fruit bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add whole eggs, bananas, flour, soda, nuts, chips and cherries.
Blend well.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 350° in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: apfel kuchen (apple cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Put mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan, building up edges slightly.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.
Remove from pan.

title: cracker meringue pie
directions: Beat eggs with baking powder until stiff, then beat in sugar gradually.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in well-buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, berries, sauce or combinations.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Break 6 slices of bread into bite size pieces; place in buttered 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Pour applesauce over bread. Dot with 1/2 of butter.
Break 6 remaining slices of bread over applesauce.
Mix milk, sugar, egg and spices in blender or with mixer; pour over bread and applesauce.
Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 350° until brown on top (approximately 30 minutes).

title: fluffy seven minute frosting
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in top part of double boiler.
Beat at low speed to mix thoroughly.
Place over boiling water and beat at high speed for 7 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat for 1 more minute to thicken spread.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: *May use cream of celery, cream of chicken or cream of mushroom soup.

title: green salad with cottage cheese
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let set while you cut up vegetables.
Then mix vegetables, cottage cheese and Miracle Whip and add to the jello.
Pour into 6 x 10-inch Pyrex dish and put in refrigerator until set.

title: upside-down date pudding cake
directions: Combine dates and boiling water.
Let stand until cool.
Cream sugars, egg and melted butter until light.
Spoon flour and all dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pan.
Combine 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Pour carefully over batter.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread separately in plastic bags.
When it is just thawed, it is most pliable.
Roll out 1 loaf Rhodes bread on 13 x 19-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle oregano and garlic on dough and cover with slices of pepperoni and then with slices of Provolone cheese.
Begin to roll from bottom right corner.
Coat rolled loaf with oil.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Pour frozen potatoes into a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Heat soup and cream cheese together until smooth.
Stir in sour cream. Pour over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle generously with grated Cheddar cheese and continue baking for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts in 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Arrange chicken in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine preserves, soy sauce, lemon juice, garlic and ginger.
Brush chicken with some preserve mixture.
Cook, covered with wax paper, on High for 14 to 18 minutes, until tender or juices run clear when pierced with a knife.
Occasionally brush chicken with preserves and rearrange halfway through cooking.
Put on rest of preserves.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Serve with hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Mix with a spoon.
Bake on a 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Wash cauliflower; remove green leaves.
Separate into flowerets, slicing large ones into bite size pieces.
Trim large leaves from broccoli; remove tough ends of lower stalks and wash broccoli thoroughly.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: old-fashioned creamy eggnog
directions: In
a
5 cup blender container, combine powdered sugar, eggs, salt
and
vanilla.
Cover.
Blend
at high speed until well blended, 15 to 20 seconds.
In a 2 quart saucepan, place 2
cups of whipping cream.
Cook over medium heat until thermometer reaches 140° (60°C) for 5 to 6 minutes.
While blending
at medium
speed,
slowly add warm whipping cream to egg mixture. Continue blending until frothy.
In the same 2 quart saucepan, stir
together egg mixture and the remaining 2 cups of
whipping cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally,
until thermometer reaches 140°.
Top each serving with sweetened whipped cream and nutmeg.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test by inserting knife in center.

title: stir-fry chicken(serves 1)
directions: In wok, combine chicken, 1/4 cup salad dressing, vegetables and seasonings; cook until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining salad dressing.
Cook for 5 minutes and serve.

title: deep freeze pickles
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together first before you start slicing onions and cucumbers.
Let stand 2 hours.
Be sure to mix this real good.
Slice cucumbers thin and onions thin.
Soak in salt and water for 2 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Pour vinegar and sugar over cucumbers and onions.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Put in freezer boxes in the freezer.
Take out and use as needed.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat to boiling point.
Pour over canned beets.
Let set in refrigerator for day or two.

title: quick and easy pork chops with gravy
directions: Fry pork chops until done.
Pour soup along with a can of water over the pork chops. Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes. Salt and pepper to your own taste.

title: okinawa doughnuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Do not overmix. To test temperature for oil, drop tiny ball of dough and if it rises to the top, oil is ready.
Pinch enough dough with tips of fingers to form small balls and deep fry.

title: fiery fettuccine
directions: Cook and drain pasta as directed on package. While pasta is cooking, place whipping cream, Creole seasoning and bell peppers in blender or food processor. Cover and blend on high speed until smooth. Pour pepper mixture into 12 inch skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens. Stir in sausage; heat through but do not boil. Serve sausage mixture over fettuccine. Sprinkle with onions.

title: grandma's cheesecake
directions: Crust: Mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar together. Add melted butter. Mix well. Press firmly in bottom of pan (spring-form cake pan is best), but not necessary. Recipe will usually fill 2 ready-made crusts.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Freeze.

title: spinach salad
directions: Microwave almonds in glass pie plates on High 2 to 3 minutes or until roasted, stirring every minute.
Arrange leaves, strawberries and almonds on salad plates.
Spoon orange-poppy seed dressing over salad.

title: strawberry jam with gelatin(sugar-free)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine strawberries and sweetener in a saucepan.
Place over high heat; stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; continue to cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in ascorbic acid powder and food coloring.
Ladle into clean jars; seal.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown the stew meat in olive oil.
Add onion and simmer 2 minutes.
Put all ingredients (except rice) in crock-pot.
Cook for 4 to 5 hours.
One hour before time to eat, add the rice.
I only use 1/2 cup rice so that there will be more liquid.
Use the liquid from the olives.
I never add any extra salt.
This stew freezes very well.
I freeze small containers for later meals.

title: hot dog chili
directions: In saucepan, boil meat until all red is gone.
Remove from heat; drain meat well.
Put meat in large pan with other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: saute of chicken with cream sauce
directions: Cut the chicken into serving portions.
Melt the butter with the oil in a large heavy frying pan.
Add chicken; fry over medium heat for about 3 minutes or until golden.
Add the wine, then bring to a simmer.
Add the stock and thyme and simmer for about 20 minutes or until thicken is tender.
Transfer chicken to a heated serving dish.
Add the cream to the liquid in frying pan; boil until mixture is consistency of heavy cream.
Add salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour over chicken.

title: chocolate lover's layer cake
directions: These are rich and wonderful when you use fresh lemon juice and real butter.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Stir in gelatin.
Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until congealed.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first five ingredients; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Cool for 5 minutes, stirring twice. Spoon into individual serving dishes. Can serve warm or chilled.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add mashed bananas.	Mix dry ingredients.
Add
to banana mixture.
Add eggs and buttermilk and vanilla.
Put
in	greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover
loosely
with
foil and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: rabbit paprikash
directions: Saute cut-up rabbit in cooking oil and margarine until browned.
Add onions and cook these until soft.
Add paprika, salt and pepper to taste and the chicken broth.
Simmer, adding water until the rabbit is done.
Add sour cream and bring to a simmer. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: soda bread
directions: *Buttermilk:
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice to milk.

title: indian relish
directions: Finely chop first 5 ingredients.
Put in large saucepan.
Blend in all other ingredients.
Simmer slowly, uncovered, until thick, about 2 hours.
Seal in pint jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening with chocolate squares.
Blend sugar with beaten eggs; mix well together.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and nutmeg; stir well.
Bake in shallow 8 x 12-inch cake pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Empty apple pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix vanilla into mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Dribble oleo over all.
Sprinkle with a little more cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold. Good with ice cream.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Saute
butter, onions and celery. Add to other ingredients. Mix
and
put into casserole dish.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with Durkee onions until brown.

title: old fashioned spaghetti
directions: Fry bacon and onion together.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Simmer about 1/2 hour to let the flavors blend.

title: oatmeal cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, eggs, molasses and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix flour, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to butter/sugar mixture.
Add oats, raisins and chocolate chips. Bake at 350°
for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: salisbury steak a la belmont
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Shape meat mixture into eight oval patties.
Sprinkle lightly with flour and brush with oil.
Broil about six minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness. Arrange on serving platter and pour Belmont Sauce over steaks.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pork chop and bean casserole
directions: Put 1/2 can beans in casserole dish, layer pork chops on top. Add salt, pepper, mustard, and ketchup. Keep layering until bowl is full, with pork and beans on top. Bake at 350° until pork chops are tender. Can be cooked in crockpot on low until tender.

title: danish fruitcake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Mix eggs, flour, soda and salt. Combine with sugar mixture. Add buttermilk, orange juice, coconut, raisins, nuts and fruit. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt sally's cocoa drops
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Add nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop with teaspoon 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with a chocolate icing.
Makes soft, fudgy cookies, studded with nuts.
Frost them if you like.
A family picnic favorite!!

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and onion; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients except cheese.
Put in Dutch oven; cover with cheese. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, margarine and vanilla. Mix well or put in blender and blend at low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cut chicken as for stewing.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours or until tender in water to which has been added salt, onion, bay leaf and parsley.
When chicken is tender, remove from broth.
Remove bones and shred meat.
Skim chicken stock.
Cook noodles for 15 to 20 minutes in stock.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a large greased glass pie pan or dish for 50 minutes at 325°.
Leave in oven 10 more minutes after heat is cut off to prevent falling.

title: shriveled lettuce
directions: Cut up lettuce and bacon.
Chop onion.
Add vinegar and sugar. Shake bowl.
Garnish with egg on top.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; add beaten egg.
Add enough buttermilk to reach desired consistency.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pretzel crust yummy
directions: Crust:
Mix pretzels and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 375°. Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill baked pie shell with strawberries.
Combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until clear.
Remove from heat and add strawberry Jell-O.
Stir well.
Cool and pour over berries. Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll out as you would biscuits. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Sprinkle sugar on top while hot.

title: chicken in cheese sauce
directions: Place chicken breasts on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together garlic powder, onion powder and pepper and spread over chicken to season.
Mix together soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: seafood au gratin
directions: Mix butter and flour, set aside.
Peel and devein shrimp. Flake crabmeat.
Combine milk, wine or milk, shrimp and crab meat in a large bowl; add cheese. Combine all together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer refried beans and sour cream.
In a blender, mix the avocados until soft, then layer on top of the beans and sour cream.
Layer the chilies, olives, onions and tomatoes.
Grate and sprinkle the cheeses on top.
Heat until cheese melts, then serve hot with chips.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add salt, raisins, sugar, nutmeg, vanilla and egg.
Mash up.
Put in small greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add lemon flavoring.
Pour batter into large tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creek bank potatoes
directions: Prepare
black skillet with enough oil to fry potatoes. Add all ingredients, fry until tender and brown.

title: speedy pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Combine water and yeast; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and salt (dough will be soft and sticky).
Using the back of a spoon, spread dough on bottom and up sides of a greased 10-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Combine tomato sauce, oregano and garlic powder; spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with sausage and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer, or until crust is browned.
Top with Parmesan and Romano cheese.
Yields one 10-inch pizza.

title: raisin pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook and stir until thick and bubbly the brown sugar, cornstarch, raisins, juices and peels.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Remove from heat and stir in the nuts.
Fill a 9-inch pie plate.
Put lattice work on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden color.

title: tim's caramel corn
directions: Spread popcorn and nuts in a large pan.
In a large saucepan stir sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat until it boils, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking without stirring for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and nuts to coat well.
Bake at 250° uncovered for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk; add instant topping, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into baked crusts and refrigerate until set or overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fruit crunch dessert
directions: Mix all together except fruit pie filling.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Spread 1 can fruit pie filling over this.
Spread remainder of mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° until crunchy and brown.
Serve with topping, if preferred. Especially good with cherry pie filling.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients, except the Rice Krispies. Next blend in Rice Krispies.
Use hands to roll into small balls and press onto greased baking sheet (press flat).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown on the bottom.

title: refried beans
directions: Drain beans. Grease nonstick pan.
Mash beans. Add salsa. Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.
This is low-fat version.

title: japanese somen salad
directions: Mix well and pour on the salad.
Toss (just before serving).

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Steam broccoli until tender but not mushy.
In heavy saucepan, melt margarine and saute onion until tender.
Add soup and celery seed.
Remove from heat and stir in pimento cheese spread, soy sauce, red pepper and nutmeg.
Mix together ham, rice and sauce.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spoon 2/3 of the rice mixture into the dish; arrange broccoli spears on top with stems toward center so that the flowerets line the edge of the dish.
Spoon remaining rice mixture in center, on top of broccoli stems.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: super salmon loaf
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add bread crumbs and milk.
Cook until crumbs are soft.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly. Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with cheese sauce or tartar sauce, if desired.

title: cherry cool whip salad
directions: Mix well with spoon and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: baked scrambled eggs
directions: Place bread and cheese	in
a 9 x 13-inch pan, layered. Add eggs beaten with
milk,
add
salt.
Pour
over
bread and cheese. Cover and	refrigerate overnight.	Next day, fry 6 to 8 slices bacon and crumble over eggs.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° until brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 450° for ten minutes. Reduce to 350°.
Bake until done.

title: norwegian coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add melted butter.
Mix and sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Turn into a shallow buttered pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies (do not remove cream), reserve 3 cups for topping.
Mix 1 cup cookies and butter. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and freeze 20 minutes.

title: green and white salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except bacon) and toss with cauliflower and broccoli.
Let marinate overnight.
Cook bacon crisp and toss just before serving.

title: chocolate wonderful
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Pack in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust. Beat puddings, milk and vanilla until thickened and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread whipped topping over pudding mixture to make final layer.
Garnish with shaved chocolate bar, if desired.

title: burger and broccoli casserole
directions: In skillet, saute onion with margarine (and soy sauce, if desired).
Add ground beef; cook until beef is brown.
Drain away excess grease.
Cook rice and broccoli separately until both are fully cooked.
Drain broccoli.
Add rice and broccoli to the 2 cans of mushroom soup in large casserole dish.
Add beef and onion; stir until well mixed.
Top with cheese.
Heat in oven at 400° until cheese is fully melted.

title: cold tomato soup
directions: Combine soup, water, sour cream.
Blend well.
Add horseradish, sherry, curry and salt to taste.
Chill.
Serves Four.

title: pecan chews
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Great for parties and large crowds.

title: creamside cake
directions: Line bottom
and
2 long sides of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with
waxed
paper.
Cut cake into 3 even slices, put them in the pan and trim remaining slices to fit pan.
Pack sherbet into cake lined
pan; top with remaining slice of pound cake. Cover with waxed paper; freeze for at least 3 hours.
Combine cream, sugar and vanilla;
beat.
Put on top of cake;
freeze until ready to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hushpuppies
directions: Mix together all ingredients just before the hushpuppies are to be cooked.
Drop by tablespoonful into 350° oil.
As long as they are not touching, hushpuppies will turn over by themselves. If they need help, flip with a spoon once, and drain on paper.

title: plum and pear compote with dates and lemon
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer, uncovered, until the fruit is tender and the liquid is reduced to roughly 1/2 cup, about 10 minutes.
Chill and serve in place of cranberry sauce with ham, turkey or other poultry.
Or for dessert, spoon it over low-fat vanilla yogurt, frozen or plain.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups, or 8 servings.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Heat sugar, water and pineapple to boiling; beat in the jello and cream cheese.
Cool.
Beat in whipping cream.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Combine egg, oil and juice.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: grandmother kolowski's fried cabbage and macaroni
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute onions and cabbage for 5 minutes or until tender.
Cook macaroni in salted boiling water. Drain and add to cabbage.
Cook 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and 1/2 cup chopped pecans together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Mix together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over first layer when cool.
Whip lemon pudding with milk until thick enough to spread over second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining pecans.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, gelatin, water and salt in pan; cook over medium heat until clear.
Cool.
Add blueberries.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Refrigerate until set. Serve with frozen whipped topping or whipped cream.
Yields 8 servings.

title: aunt ethel's molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses and beat again.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Roll out on floured breadboard and cut cookie shapes desired.
Bake in a 375° oven until done, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and onion until done; drain.
Add mayo and cheese; mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Crumble crackers over top of casserole.
Put butter on crackers; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: almond cheesecake with raspberries
directions: Stir together crumbs, margarine and sugar in small bowl; press into bottom and 1/2 inch side of spring-form pan or pie plate. Chill.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
In saucepan, combine cocoa, water and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 16 (approximately) pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, beans, sour cream, cheese, onion and soups.
Pour in casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour butter over crackers and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cream butter and salt.
Add eggs.
Add chilies, corn and cheese.
Sift flour.
Mix in cornmeal, baking powder and salt to flour.
Add dry mixture to butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and egg.
Add dry ingredients and pineapple.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Frost with mixture of 3/4 cup powdered sugar thinned with pineapple juice saved from can. Drizzle over warm cookies.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from fire; pour over beaten egg yolk and add butter and lemon juice.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots; add raisins.
Mix well.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Make cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Make pudding, using 3 cups milk.
Beat together.
Add 1 cup Kahlua; beat until mixed.
Cut cooled cake into squares.
Put on bottom layer of bowl.
Pour 1/2 pudding mix on top, then layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle 1/2 of crumbled Heath bars on top of Cool Whip.
Start over with layer of chocolate cake.
End with candy on top.

title: sausage stuffing for turkey
directions: Pan-fry sausage until browned.
Mix with other ingredients. Makes enough for 14-pound turkey.

title: chinese chewies
directions: Beat eggs; add next ingredients. Mix well. Add flour slowly. Dough should be somewhat thin. Add remaining ingredients. Dough should be thick enough to hold together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 8 minutes or until edges are light brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add Wesson oil and eggs.
Add carrots and mix well.
Bake in two-9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: easy tamale casserole
directions: Unwrap the tamales and lay them in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Heat the hominy and pour over the tamales.
Drain the hominy.
Sprinkle with chili powder. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Cover with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: apple dumpling sauce
directions: Boil 3 minutes and pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and juice thickens.
Makes enough for 4 dumplings.

title: spicy baked carrots
directions: Slice carrots diagonally and arrange in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Thoroughly cream butter, sugar, cinnamon, salt and pepper; mix in water.
Pour butter mixture over sliced carrots.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat for about 3 to 5 minutes until sauce is well mixed.
Remove from heat.
Sauce can be poured over meat or each piece of meat can be dipped individually in the sauce.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute in oil:
onions, celery, drained bean sprouts and drained water chestnuts.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add cornstarch and soy sauce to liquid drained from sprouts and chestnuts, blending until smooth.
Add broth, sugar and parsley to sauteed vegetables; add chicken and last add the cornstarch-soy mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles (leftover pork or beef also can be used).

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream and spices. Spread in 9 or 10-inch quiche or pie dish.
Spread pizza sauce over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese. Bake for 5 minutes.
Serve with green pepper strips, broccoli flowerets, plain nacho chips or crackers.

title: choco chip cream cheese dessert
directions: Roll out half of the dough on bottom of glass 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs and spread evenly on top of dough. Roll the other half of dough and place as top layer. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and cut into bars like brownies.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Soak chicken in buttermilk 2 hours.
Blend remaining ingredients until fine and coat chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, uncovered, in pan sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini and drain.
Dice next 3 ingredients.
Toss together with Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Marinate 24 hours for a better flavor.

title: dried beef log
directions: Mix together in small bowl until smooth.
Shape with spoon into log shape.
Coat in chopped dried beef.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Boil
sugar,
syrup
and
water on medium heat until it reaches
a
hard boil stage (255°).
Remove from heat and pour into
the
stiffly
beaten
egg whites.
Beat constantly until mixture
holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop quickly from spoon onto wax paper.

title: zucchini with meat sauce
directions: Cook onions and pepper in small amount of salad oil until soft. Add ground beef.
Brown it.
Pour off drippings.
Add and mix in flour.
Add canned tomatoes.
Stir.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Put sliced zucchini in casserole.
Cover with tomato-meat mixture and bake uncovered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: amy's casserole
directions: Mix, cover with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: apple tart
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and half and half.
Pour over apples that were placed in pie shell.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Take off foil and bake 15 minutes more.

title: oriental chicken and peanuts
directions: Marinate chicken with beaten egg white, 3 teaspoons cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Refrigerate several hours.
Saute chicken in oil 3 to 4 minutes, until lightly browned.
Blend in remaining ingredients, holding vegetables aside.
Add vegetables and 1/2 cup peanuts, just to heat.
Serve immediately over rice. Serves 4.

title: enchiladas
directions: Melt milk, soup, cheese, dip and tomatoes.
Brown hamburger meat; add onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper, mix with other. Heat tortillas in a skillet with oil.
Place meat mixture in each tortilla, roll and place in baking dish.
Pour leftover mixture over top and bake 30 minutes at 350° covered with foil.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm and combine it with sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, soda and eggs.
Add softened yeast.

title: grandma's stuffed peppers
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, pepper, salt, chopped onions, egg, milk and tomato paste.
Stuff cleaned peppers.
Place in a pressure cooker and add water or tomato juice.
Cook 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: busy day oven stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer meat and onion.
Add bay leaves.
In a medium bowl, stir water, wine, flour, lemon juice, bouillon granules, garlic, salt and pepper until blended.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake for 3 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Add well thawed stew vegetables; stir.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat until fluffy.
Gradually add milk; beat well.
Add lemon juice and beat until well blended. Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust and chill.
Pour pie filling on top for fruit lovers or put in fruit bowl on the side for everyone to help themselves.

title: black bean soup
directions: In a large, heavy soup pot, place all ingredients except sour cream. Bring to a boil. Turn heat down and simmer for about 3 hours or until beans are tender.
Add more water as needed and stir occasionally.
Make sure there is enough water in pot to make soup consistency and not too thick.
Place a few cups at a time in a food processor (using the steel blade) or the blender and puree it until it is smooth.
Add sour cream and reheat soup. Serve in individual bowls.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick. While hot, add jello. Cool and add blackberries. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate. When set, top with small Cool Whip.

title: beef stew with olive oil
directions: In a heavy, covered saucepan, brown meat very slowly in hot oil for 20 minutes.
Add spices and cook 2 hours.
Remove bay leaves, then add diced onion and carrots.
Cook approximately. Leave liquid as is or remove and thicken.
(If refrigerated first, additional fat may be skimmed from top.)

title: crescent rolls
directions: In a saucepan put milk, sugar and salt.
Heat until melted. When cool, add to beaten egg and dissolved yeast.
Add enough flour until dough is too stiff to beat.
Cover and let rise double.
Push down and roll out.
Cut.
Brush 1/2 of circle with melted butter.
Fold over.
Let rise 20 minutes in a greased pan. Bake at 450°.
Watch.

title: beans and pasta
directions: In a medium size pot, heat oil and saute garlic over medium heat.
Add tomatoes and Ro-Tel.
Stir.
Add basil, salt and pepper.
Cook for approximately 45 minutes, stirring every five minutes.
Add beans and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Toss with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: canned sauerkraut
directions: Quality:
For the best sauerkraut, use firm heads of fresh cabbage.
Shred cabbage and start kraut between 24 and 48 hours after harvest.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Combine peaches and 3/4 cup of sugar; let stand 20 minutes or place in saucepan on low heat to dissolve sugar.
Melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sift flour and 1 cup of sugar together. Add milk and stir briskly.
Some lumps will remain.
Pour into dish of melted margarine.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine; combine other ingredients in large bowl (except nuts).
Pour margarine over flour mix and beat until smooth.
Add nuts.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg at low speed until crumbly.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over this.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise and sauerkraut; mix well.
Place in an 8-inch pie plate or baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with rye crackers.

title: party punch for children
directions: Partially defrost the lemonade and strawberries.

Pour ingredients into punch bowl, adding the ginger ale last. Strawberries, mint leaves and pineapple chunks can be frozen in a ring of Hawaiian Punch and floated in the center of the bowl for a special touch.

title: chicken salad
directions: Bake frozen chicken breasts.
Use food processor - press 3-4 times to grind chicken.
Add celery, onion and grind in processor. Mix those ingredients and the remaining ingredients.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Add the water.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in boiling water until tender.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in drained yellow squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix with butter.
Spread half of the stuffing mix in a square casserole dish (12 x 7-inch).
Spoon vegetable mixture over this and then top with the remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: friendship tea
