directions: Mix well and use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
I like this when I have a cold.

title: pineapple crush cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box for a sheet cake; let cool. Beat cream cheese, pudding mix and milk for 2 minutes; set aside. Poke holes in top of cake and spread pineapple on top.
Frost cake. Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; beat in milk and oil until smooth.
Pour into ungreased baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 12 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange peaches on top.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon; sprinkle on top of peaches.
Bake until pick inserted in center comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes in 350° oven. Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, dry jello, drained pineapple and drained oranges.
Mix everything together and refrigerate.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix chicken, 1/2 cup sour cream and most of the cheese; set aside.
In
large
frying pan, saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon
oil
until
translucent.
Add
tomatoes,
chilies, water and
spices.
Simmer to taste with more spices.
Put 1/2 cup sauce
in
with
chicken
mixture.
Then
add 1/2 cup sour cream to
sauce.
Put
approximately 2 tablespoons chicken on each tortilla.
Roll and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When all 12 tortillas are
in
the pan, pour rest of sauce over top and sprinkle with
leftover
cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: raspberry swirl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 10-inch fluted tart pan with removable bottom with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare brownie mix by the directions for cake like brownies.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of boiling salted water for about 6 to 8 minutes; drain.
Combine celery, water chestnuts, soup, pimiento and salt; mix well and pour the mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine noodles or crackers with almonds and butter; sprinkle over celery mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tuna-stuffed shells in dill sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 11 x 17-inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Blend crackers and butter; spread half of mixture in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt marshmallows in milk and cool.
Add whipped cream and pour half of this mixture over graham crust. Refrigerate for 30 minutes or more.
Pour pie filling over marshmallow layer.
Add remaining marshmallow mixture and top with remaining graham cracker mix.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 9.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in warm water.
Add mayonnaise and vanilla. Mix flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Mix together the flour mixture and cocoa mixture until smooth, but don't overbeat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in the middle.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet with butter, then place graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Bring to a boil the butter and sugar; boil for approximately 2 minutes.
Add nuts to butter, then drizzle all over tops of graham crackers.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Let set in pan 1 minute after removing from oven.
Remove and put on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: cran-apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl combine apples, cranberries, orange juice and orange peel.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a medium bowl combine flour, oatmeal, sugar, spices and oil until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake 25 minutes, until apples are tender and top is golden.
Serve warm with plain or vanilla yogurt, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: light chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Place flour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until the color of caramel, stirring flour every 5 minutes.
Brown sausage in a Dutch oven coated with cooking spray over medium heat.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe drippings from Dutch oven.
Brown chicken; drain and pat dry. Wipe drippings from Dutch oven.
Cook onion, green pepper and celery in a Dutch oven coated with cooking spray until tender. Sprinkle with browned flour.
Gradually stir in water; bring to a boil.
Add chicken, garlic and next 5 ingredients.
Reduce heat. Simmer mixture, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Remove chicken; let cool. Add sausage and cook gumbo, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir in green onions.
Cook uncovered an additional 30 minutes.
Bone chicken and cut into strips.
Add to gumbo and cook until heated.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
2 quarts (eight 1-cup servings).

title: meatless stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Finely chop stems (about 1/2 cup) and set aside.
Do the same with red and green pepper. In large skillet, saute onion, mushroom stems and pepper until soft.
Keep mixture very moist adding more butter as you need it. Add bread crumbs until mixture holds together.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, sage and thyme.
Spoon on to mushroom caps. Bake on cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir all together until blended.
Spread in greased pan.
May be iced for added flavor.

title: sushi "alive"
directions: Place the sesame seeds, cashews and lentil sprouts in a food processor and process until thick and meaty.
Add the carrot, pepper, and celery and process until smooth.
Add the olive oil, cabbage and tamari and process until the cabbage is chopped but not liquified.
The cabbage should add some texture to the mixture.
Spread approximately 1/2 cup filling on the lower half of a sheet of nori.
Add a line of sliced tomatoes and sprouts. Roll and eat immediately or wrap in a plastic wrap and store until ready to use.
As the sushi sits, nori becomes less crunchy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and parboil squash for 5 minutes; drain and set aside. Mix in a large bowl, soup, sour cream and onion.
Stir into drained squash.
Melt margarine in skillet and stir into stuffing mix.
Put squash into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, top with stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon squares(good)
directions: Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange pineapple sherbet(sugar-free)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Beat on low speed about 5 minutes or until dry milk is mixed in.
Then beat on high speed until mixture is thick and foamy, about 5 minutes. Freeze according to your freezer directions.

title: buttery biscuit rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add sour cream and flour to butter; mix.
Drop batter into miniature, ungreased muffin tins.
Fill to the top.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: caramel pecan pinwheels
directions: In a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan, stir together
the ice cream topping and melted margarine. Sprinkle with the pecans. Separate, but do not uncoil, the bread sticks.
Arrange coils atop caramel mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 2 to 3 minutes.
Loosen sides and invert rolls onto a serving plate. Serve warm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Pick over, wash berries and put through coarse grinder.
Add water.
Cook to boiling and boil 10 minutes.
Add sugar; let mixture come to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Pour into molds and chill.

title: apple salad
directions: Blend the margarine, pineapple, sugar and flour and cook until thick.
Cool.
Stir the chopped apples, one at a time, into the mixture.
Spread into an oblong dish (about 7 x 10 inches) and top with Cool Whip, pecans and maraschino cherries.

title: million dollar pie(doris bryant)
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk, drained pineapple and nuts, then add lemon juice.
Stir until thick.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle coconut on top and press into pie.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: bran nut bread
directions: Beat eggs in an ice cream pail. Add soft butter and buttermilk, mixing well. Add cereal, sugar, flour, soda and chopped pecans, blending well after each. Cover with the lid. Refrigerated batter will keep for 1 month.

title: lemon-carrot bundles
directions: Cut carrots into 3-inch julienne sticks.
Arrange carrots on a steaming rack and place over boiling water.
Cover and steam 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove carrots and plunge into ice water to stop the cooking process.
Drain.
Separate carrots into 6 bundles.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine soups, sour cream and onions.
Add mixture to frozen potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Use rectangular glass dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs with salad oil. Stir in sugar. Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to oil and sugar.
Add apples, walnuts and vanilla. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done. (For a Pyrex dish, bake at 325°.)
Frost cake while warm.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until it boils at medium heat for 2 minutes.
Test with very cold water for soft ball stage, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir with pan in cold water until it starts to thicken.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Cool and cut.
You may exchange peanut butter fudge by taking out the cocoa.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Arrange spinach leaves and strawberries on serving plate or bowl.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix with soup, milk, tuna, cheese and onion.
Pour into a greased 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly (or at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes).

title: oriental oven fried pork chops
directions: Combine egg, soy sauce and sherry in a shallow pan.
Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Add chops to egg mixture.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Combine bread crumbs, garlic powder and ginger. Dredge chops in bread crumb mix.
Arrange in pan coated with spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: magic bars
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter.
Pat in an 11 x 9-inch pan. Put chips and coconut in layers in pan.
Pour milk over mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate jumbo cookies
directions: Blend as usual and drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350°. Trash if desired.

title: stir-fry kielbasa
directions: Saute chopped onion and green pepper and meat (cut up) until browned.
Make sauce with rest of ingredients except pineapple. Stir into meat mixtures.
Lastly add drained pineapple chunks. Cook until heated.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: pineapple pick-me-up
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine pineapple juice, ice cream, tea and sugar. Beat until thoroughly blended. Gradually add milk. Pour into glasses and garnish with pineapple wedges, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit, then mix well and chill overnight.
Fruit cocktail can be substituted for pineapple.

title: pepper relish
directions: Scald all ingredients for 5 minutes. Drain and boil in vinegar for 1/2 hour.
Jar and seal.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Boil the mixture 5 minutes before putting on cake.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Bring to boil in water first 5 ingredients.
When noodles are done drain off water.
Remove noodles to a separate container. Into vegetable mixture add next 6 ingredients, mix well with spaghetti sauce.
Layer vegetable mixture in a large casserole bowl with noodles and cheese.
Casserole must end with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese starts to brown.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes on stove for a short time in salt water.
Also in another pot, mix ingredients on stove and pour over sweet potatoes in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: california overnight rolls
directions: Mix and let stand for 1/2 hour the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, flour, salt and butter.
Knead lightly and place in large bowl.
Cover bowl with Saran Wrap.
Let stand overnight without refrigeration.
The next morning, divide dough into three parts. Roll each part into 9-inch circle.
Cut into 8 pie wedges.
Roll each wedge, starting at wide end.
Form into a crescent shape. Repeat with the rest of the dough.
Place on well-greased cookie sheets and let raise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 9 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Fold dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine sliced pickles, onion, green pepper and salt together; let stand 2 hours.
Stir together sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Drain pickles and add vinegar syrup; let cool.
Put in freezer containers or will keep in the refrigerator up to 1 month.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Advance preparation:
Thoroughly cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Add corn syrup and orange peel; mix well.
Stir flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt together thoroughly; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough thoroughly.

title: hot rolls
directions: Stir as you go.
Let rise until double.
Punch down, shape into rolls and put into greased pan.
Let rise again, then bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in baking dish.
Season pork chops and place on top of mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, covered, at 325°. Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well.
Rinse with cold water.
Chill.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Set aside 3 shrimp for garnish.
Coarsely chop remainder. Combine cream cheese and remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Stir in chopped shrimp.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Place in serving bowl and garnish with whole shrimp.
Serve with assorted crackers. Yield:
1 1/4 cups.

title: russian stuffed eggs
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter for 8 to 10 minutes, until limp and golden, but not brown.
In another skillet, saute bread crumbs in remaining 1 tablespoon butter, stirring until just golden.
(Dark crumbs will taste bitter, so be careful not to let them become too dark.)

title: frittata(mexicali corn 'n beef)
directions: Whisk eggs in bowl with red pepper sauce and sprinkling of salt and pepper; set aside.
In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, break ground beef into medium to small lumps.
Slowly brown beef, chopped onion, green pepper and chili powder.
Drain all grease from skillet.
Add to skillet the drained corn, tomato, olives and sprinkling of salt and pepper; add flour and mix well.
Turn heat to simmer; pour eggs mixture evenly over all.
Do not stir.
Cover skillet and cook slowly for 4 to 5 minutes or until eggs are almost set.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread between layers, on top and sides.
Sprinkle with pecans and walnuts.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip peanut butter balls into the chocolate.
Place balls on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Put in freezer (remove toothpicks) for 2 minutes.
Remove from freezer and store in container.
Makes about 500 balls, depending on size you roll them into.

title: bear paws
directions: Melt together chocolate and butter.
Beat together eggs, flour, sugar and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on hot waffle iron.
Bake one minute.
Cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Use pecans for claws.

title: jello
directions: Add jello to boiling apple juice and stir until it completely dissolves.
Add water.
Add sliced bananas.

title: lemon-pineapple jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Mix in jello.
Cut up cream cheese and stir into mixture (does not have to be completely blended).
Put in refrigerator to cool, then beat well with mixer. Put in Cool Whip and chill overnight.

title: seven-layer refrigerator salad
directions: In a medium-sized bowl with a tight fitting lid, shred lettuce.
Mix together onion, celery and pepper.
Place these vegetables in a layer on top of lettuce.
Add English peas as next layer.
Beat enough mayonnaise to make a layer 1/4-inch deep over the peas.
Sprinkle the sugar over mayonnaise layer; add grated cheese layer and sprinkle bacon crumbs on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients 4 times, or mix extra well.
Make hole in center.
Add the mayonnaise, boiling water and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until done.

title: fish fry potato salad
directions: Drain potatoes and onion.
Add eggs, olives, pickles and bacon bits, chopped as coarse or as fine as you want.
Mix with Ranch dressing and let sit for about an hour.
Just before serving, mix in the mayo to make it moist.
Makes a family size bowl.

title: carrot-apple salad
directions: In a large serving dish, mix the ingredients together.
A real advantage of this recipe is that measurements don't have to be exact, and you can change the ratio of the carrots to apples to suit your taste.
Try pineapple instead of apples for a variation.

title: streusel filled coffee cake
directions: Mix together with fork sugar, cinnamon, flour, butter and chopped nuts before mixing Coffee Cake.
Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Blend well.
Beat egg and mix in.
Spread half of batter in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Streusel Mixture. Add other half of batter and sprinkle rest of Streusel Mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together.
Cream in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in
water until tender.
Cool; remove skin and bone.
In some
of the broth simmer onion, bell pepper and celery. In
remaining
broth
cook
spaghetti
until
tender, adding more water
as
necessary.
In another pan empty tomato soup, mushroom soup
and
oleo;
heat and add Velveeta cheese. Stir until melted. Mix everything with spaghetti.
Great meal with crackers.

title: good christmas candy
directions: Fix fruit and nuts; set aside.
Combine sugar, syrup, cream and salt; bring to boil, stirring until all sugar is dissolved. Stop stirring.
Continue boiling until mixture forms medium hard ball in cold water or 231°.
Remove from heat and beat immediately with electric mixer.
Beat until thick and creamy and candy holds form.
Add vanilla, fruit and nuts.
Press in glass pans or pans lined with foil.
Let cool and cut.
This is moist and keeps for weeks.
Makes 4 pounds.
Better as it ages.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking soda; add bacon, egg and margarine.
Mix well (machine recommended).
Gently add corn flakes.
Drop by tablespoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: bob lewis' peanut butter sandwich
directions: Put water on stove.
When it starts to boil, decide you don't want macaroni and throw it away.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, onion soup mix or onion.
Cook and drain off grease.
Layer beef, potatoes and soup in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Add grated cheese over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts and lightly browns.

title: chicken in sherry creme
directions: Heat butter in frying pan.
Mix salt and cayenne papper with some flour.
Dredge chicken pieces through flour mixture and brown.
Reduce heat and cook 20 minutes or until cooked and tender.
Remove chicken from pan and keep warm.
Add cream and sherry to pan and stir until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce and stir.
Pour sauce over fried chicken and serve immediately.

title: macaroni, ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Melt butter and stir in the next three ingredients.
Gradually add the milk and cook, stirring until thickened, then boil for about 1 minute.
Add the next three ingredients and mix with the macaroni.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Put about 1/2 of the mixture in the dish.
Pour the sour cream and cottage cheese on top of this, then add the rest of macaroni.
Add diced meat and spread it out evenly. Sprinkle with the Cheese Crumb Topping.

title: confetti fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; toss gently.
Cover and chill until ready to eat.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail well.
Then add remaining ingredients. Mix well and place in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over low heat. Burns easily.

title: crab bacon roll-ups
directions: Saute
the
onion
in butter;
remove the onion and set aside. Add
the
crabmeat
and
seasonings, tossing crab long enough
to absorb
all
of the butter.
Cut the bacon in half crosswise and roll about 1 teaspoon of crabmeat in each slice, fastening
with a toothpick.
Place the rolls on an ungreased pan;
broil until the bacon crisps.
Drain well and serve hot. These
may
be prepared well in advance and broiled when ready to serve.

title: essie's berry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together magarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir together the dry ingredients and stir into shortening mixture along with milk.
Beat until smooth and pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Smooth.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and salt.
Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until soft mounds form.
Add 3/4 cup sugar gradually. Beat until stiff peaks form.

title: sopaipillas(puffy fried bread)
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to make a soft dough just firm enough to roll.
Cover bowl and let stand for 30 to 60 minutes or refrigerate until needed.
Divide dough in half; roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board and cut into diamond-shaped pieces.
Heat oil in frying pan to approximately 370°.
Add a few pieces of dough at a time; turn at once so they will puff evenly, then turn back to brown both sides.
Drain on paper toweling.
Serve hot with butter and honey.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onions together until brown.
Drain.
Mix soups together and add to ground beef and onions.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Add to soup mixture. Mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Last 10 minutes, top with grated Cheddar cheese and crackers.

title: russian cabbage soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in Dutch oven until tender. Add beef broth, water, cabbage, carrots, potatoes and celery.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Top each serving with sour cream and garnish with parsley.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, green pepper, celery in butter or margarine over simmer burner until soft but not brown. Stir in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and shrimp.
Turn burner on full and heat to boiling. Serve over rice.

title: cheese con queso
directions: Stir and serve hot.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine.
Toss with dressing.
Garnish with chopped, hard-boiled egg, if desired.
Mix dressing ingredients in blender:

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugar with a fork.
Add vanilla and a little of the flour.
Turn on board and work the rest of flour in with hands.
Break off small piece at a time and roll into a ball. Place balls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass.
Bake in a 250° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Will be very light in color.
Let cool completely.
Store in airtight containers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put the well drained corn in the bottom of a buttered 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole and set aside.
In a bowl, mix together the sugar, flour and salt; set aside.
In another bowl, beat the eggs. Add the milk and softened butter and mix well.
Pour the egg mixture into the bowl with the flour mixture and blend well.
Add lemon extract, mix well and pour over the corn in the casserole. Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well. Stir in flour.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into 1/2-inch of hot oil. Cook until browned, turning once.
Drain.
Yields 6 servings.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle nuts and chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not use mixer. Bake in sheet cake pan, well greased and floured, at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Does not need icing.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Add cranberries, water, cinnamon sticks, nutmeg, orange juice and zest to stockpot.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cranberries will be soft and water will be cranberry color when ready.

title: lazy woman's pie
directions: In pie pan, melt butter.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour into pie pan.
Then pour fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chilies, enchilada sauce and drained olives.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Slice
and
layer
potatoes
with
other ingredients in large casserole dish.
Blend mayonnaise and cheese for sauce. Pour over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh navy bean stew
directions: Saute Sofrito, sasson and tomato sauce.
Add beans and pumpkin.
Cook over low heat until broth thickens.
Season to taste and remove from heat.
Serve with chicken and rice or with white rice.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Boil apples at medium-high temperature.
Pour apples into a bowl; put sugar in them.
Put butter in them.
Then stir until butter and sugar not shone.
Roll your dough for crust in size you like.
Put apples into crust.
Then fold the other side over to cover apples.
Poke the sides of the crust or mash with a fork. Put grease in a pan until hot; put turnovers into pan.
Let fry until brown and flip.
Put in a strainer to strain grease.

title: ice cream mix
directions: Add milk to fill to about 3/4 of 4-quart container.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and walnuts.
Blend together mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold into apple mixture. Chill.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in large glass bowl in microwave. Stir chow mein noodles and peanuts in until coated.
Spoon haystacks onto wax paper and let cool.
These are great for children to make.

title: slaw
directions: Mix all the ingredients
in
a
large
bowl.
This slaw will keep up to 4 weeks in a covered bowl in the refrigerator.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and peppers in a small amount of oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain fat, and then add tomatoes, tomato sauce and beans.
Mix well.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Mix the cornbread mix according to directions on package and pour over bean mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven (preheated) until golden brown and bubbly, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lentil pea soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight.
Drain.
Insert cloves halfway into onion.
Add to pot with peas and next five ingredients.
Boil, skim off foam and simmer until cooked.
Remove bay leaf, garlic and onion.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Serve.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix together and dip hot dogs into mixture.
Fry in hot fat until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 X 13 pan. partially cook broccoli, drain. Cut each slice of bread with a doughnut cutter. Fit scraps into baking dish. Layer cheese, broccoli and ham over bread scraps. Sprinkle with onion. Arrange "doughnuts" on top. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over bread. Cover. Refrigerate at least 6 hours. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Cut so each piece has a doughnut on top. 12 servings.

title: barbecue pizza
directions: Roll out bread dough into pizza-size circle.
Put oil and foil on one side.
Cook on barbecue grill over medium heat, oil side down until golden brown.
Put toppings on cooked side (sauce, toppings and cheese).
Place on grill again and cook until golden brown.

title: braised vegetables with couscous
directions: In nonstick Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add onions, carrots, celery and zucchini.
Cook over high heat, stirring frequently until onions are lightly browned.
Add 3 cups water, chickpeas, bouillon, cumin and dash of pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Cook and crumble sausage.
Mix ingredients well and shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Can freeze for later use.

title: dream cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients. Form into balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: crab mousse dip
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into bowl.
Chill. Yum!

title: caramel icing
directions: Stir sugar, cream and butter together over low heat.
Just as soon as the mixture starts to boil, remove from heat and add powdered sugar and flavoring.
Beat until smooth enough to spread.

title: condensed milk
directions: Combine all in blender until well blended.
Refrigerate until used.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Add beaten egg to sweet potatoes.
Form into 8 balls with a marshmallow in the center of each ball.
Roll in corn flakes and deep fry.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix together oil, dressing mix and dill.
Mix with crackers and peanuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 250°.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt butter; stir in milk and vanilla.
Gradually add mixture of cocoa and confectioners sugar.
Mix by hand until soft and creamy.
Add nuts.
Press into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: caramel box pie - baked nut crust
directions: Place unopened can of sweetened condensed milk in boiling water.
Simmer for 3 hours to caramelize.
Cool.

title: pumpkin wheat muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring only to moisten. Spray 12 muffin cups with vegetable cooking spray and fill evenly. Bake 20 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion.
Drain.
Add soup and stir up.
Pour 1/2 broccoli mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour in corn bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Sprinkle half of the corn bread over the broccoli mixture.
Add all the Velveeta cheese.
Top with remaining broccoli; then with remaining corn bread.
Top with the Parmesan cheese and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: porcupines
directions: Make meat ball with ingredients and brown lightly.
Add 2 cans crushed tomato sauce and 1 can water.
Cover tightly and simmer 30 minutes until rice is tender.

title: cocoa cupcakes
directions: In bowl mix sugar, shortening, cocoa, milk and egg together. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and add boiling water.

title: beef and tater squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except the potatoes and cheese and mix well.
Pat meat into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove meat from oven and drain excess fat from dish.
Combine the hot potatoes with 3/4 cup grated cheese and spread over meat.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: minced clam dip
directions: Mix all together with juice, then add clams.
Broil until hot and serve on crackers.

title: black beans and rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat; add onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Add beans, broth and water, tomatoes, thyme, bay leaf, oregano and hot pepper sauce.
Over high heat, bring to a boil . Reduce heat; simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally until sauce thickens and vegetables are tender.
If mixture becomes too thick, add water to thin to desired consistency.
Stir in cilantro and season with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice, sprinkled with parsley.

title: honey apple muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
In another bowl, combine honey, egg, milk and oil.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Blend in apple.
Grease 2 muffin tins liberally.
Pour in lumpy batter to fill 2/3 of each cup. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove tins to a rack; let stand for 5 minutes.
Use a greased knife to cut around each cup. Tap to remove muffins.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add tomato paste and seasonings. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes; stir frequently. Press biscuits up sides of muffin pan. Spoon meat mixture in them and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: puffball or quick tea doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquid.
Beat thoroughly and add melted fat.
Add more flour to make a batter stiff enough to hold a spoon in a standing position.
Drop by spoonsful into deep fat at 375°.
Remove when brown and drain on absorbent paper towel.
Yield approximately 4 dozen.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix together cream cheese and garlic powder.
Spread on 10, 11 or 12-inch plate.
Spread cocktail sauce with onion in it evenly over cream cheese.
Put crabmeat on top (sprinkle).
Use low salt Club crackers to dip.
This spread looks like a pizza!

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in water.
When done, take chicken out and pull off bone.
Pour noodles into the water the chicken came out of and boil until done, then add all of the other ingredients in with noodles and add chicken.
Let it simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then serve while hot.

title: cocktail spread
directions: Quick and easy.
Place cream cheese in shallow serving bowl. Combine clams and cocktail sauce.
Pour over cream cheese.
Chill. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: spam-a-roni
directions: Mix tomato sauce and cut Italian tomatoes.
Add parsley flakes, oregano, garlic salt, pepper and basil leaves.
Fry ground meat and dice onion and green pepper.
Add sliced mushrooms.
When done, add to tomato sauce.
Cut Spam into small cubes.
Add to sauce.
Boil elbows.
Add to sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat and serve.

title: great shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup to boil (not water). Mix in cheese, onions, celery and mayonnaise.
Add gelatin, the water and then the shrimp. Mix well and put in a mold.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add ground beef, breaking apart with fork.
Drain off excess fat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for approximately 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!

title: brandy slush
directions: Combine sugar and water and cook until sugar is dissolved; let cool.
Make tea with tea bags and water and let cool.
Mix all together, pour into ice cream pail.
Freeze at least overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed potatoes with other ingredients; mix well. Pour into a buttered dish.

title: elegant chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add rice and soups; stir thoroughly.
Place chicken on top and season with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, until light brown.
This is an all-time family favorite.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 8)
directions: In baking dish, put layer of 1/2 of the cracker crumbs that have been mixed with melted margarine.
Then put layer of 1/2 of broccoli, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 sour cream.
Repeat last 3 layers. Top with remaining half of the cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbles.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In large pan, combine brown sugar, syrup, margarine, salt and cream of tartar and bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Add baking soda; beat down.
Pour over popcorn. Stir until all corn is covered.
Spread popcorn onto 2 greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Cool and break up and store in large plastic bags.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump and spread pie filling. Dump and spread pineapple and juice over it.
Dump and spread cake mix evenly over that.
Drizzle melted oleo over cake mix.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: brown edge wafers
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten egg and flour alternately, then vanilla and salt.
Drop in teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into popsicle molds.
Freeze.

title: mom's potato dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Top with melted margarine mixed with 2 cups crushed cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat 3 cups of milk in top of double boiler.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat egg yolks and 2 tablespoons of milk; add to sugar mixture.
Stir in hot milk; cook until thickened. Remove from heat; add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.

title: prize winning pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour in pastry-lined pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in a medium size sheet cake pan, then mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour fruit over melted margarine, then pour sugar, flour and milk mixture over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken patties or balls
directions: Soak the Japanese mushrooms in warm water for 15 minutes. Squeeze dry and chop fine.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Pour vinegar in electric skillet; add remaining ingredients. Boil rapidly for two minutes.
Turn off heat and let cool in pan. Refrigerate.

title: salmon sandwiches
directions: Flake salmon and mix with salad dressing, celery, pickle and salt.
Spread between slices of bread.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients, except kidney beans.
Simmer uncovered 2 to 3 hours.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put the tomatoes in a saucepan and cook slowly about 1 hour. Put the pepper and onion through a chopper and add to the tomatoes. Cook another 20 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients. Boil until thick (about 20 minutes).
Makes 3 pints.

title: zucchini dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon pull apart
directions: Open cans of biscuits.
Cut biscuit dough into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in Ziploc bag.
Coat pieces by shaking in bag. In greased Bundt pan, put nuts and raisins, then the coated pieces, alternating until done.
Melt brown sugar and butter, then pour over cubes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool slightly, then invert onto plate.
Now the nuts and raisins are on top.

title: hopping john
directions: Cook bacon in medium saucepan until crisp.
Add onion and celery; cook and stir until browned.
Add black-eyed peas with liquid.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add water; bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork and serve hot.
